<graph edgedefault="undirected"><node id="&quot;AN ORGANIZATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The organization is implied to be involved in wildlife conservation efforts, given the context of anti-poaching and research in Africa."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-07580d38adc683ab61ef1dfa9a6f1ef8</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CHARLES RICHET&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Charles Richet is a Nobel Laureate known for his work in physiology and medicine, specifically in the field of reflexes and the study of the stability of living beings."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-07580d38adc683ab61ef1dfa9a6f1ef8</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TARANGIRE RIVER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Tarangire River is a river located in northern Tanzania, serving as a geographical landmark for the narrator's location."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-07580d38adc683ab61ef1dfa9a6f1ef8</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NORTHERN TANZANIA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Northern Tanzania is the specific region where the narrator is conducting research, characterized by wooded bluffs and the Tarangire River."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-07580d38adc683ab61ef1dfa9a6f1ef8</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ANTI-POACHING EFFORTS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Anti-Poaching Efforts are implied to be ongoing, focusing on protecting rhinos from poaching for their horns."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-07580d38adc683ab61ef1dfa9a6f1ef8</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RHINO HORNS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Rhino Horns are valuable in the Orient as expensive aphrodisiacs, driving poaching despite the availability of alternative medications."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-07580d38adc683ab61ef1dfa9a6f1ef8</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SNAPPING TREE LIMBS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Snapping Tree Limbs is the sound that woke the narrator from sleep, indicating some disturbance in the environment."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-07580d38adc683ab61ef1dfa9a6f1ef8</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FRONT SCREEN OF TENT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The Front Screen of Tent is a part of the narrator's shelter, allowing them to see outside while sleeping."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-07580d38adc683ab61ef1dfa9a6f1ef8</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DEEP SLEEP&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"STATE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Deep Sleep is the state the narrator was in before being awakened by the sounds outside."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-07580d38adc683ab61ef1dfa9a6f1ef8</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PITCH-BLACK NIGHT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ENVIRONMENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Pitch-Black Night describes the darkness outside the tent, with no moonlight visible."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-07580d38adc683ab61ef1dfa9a6f1ef8</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HEAVY FOOTSTEPS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"SOUND"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Heavy Footsteps are the sounds heard outside the tent, possibly indicating movement around the camp."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-07580d38adc683ab61ef1dfa9a6f1ef8</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CRUNCHING NOISES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"SOUND"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Crunching Noises are the sounds of footsteps crunching on the ground, indicating someone or something moving around the camp."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-07580d38adc683ab61ef1dfa9a6f1ef8</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;OCCASIONAL LOW RUMBLING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"SOUND"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Occasional Low Rumbling is described as almost purring noises, possibly indicating the presence of large animals or vehicles."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-07580d38adc683ab61ef1dfa9a6f1ef8</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PURRING NOISES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"SOUND"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Purring Noises are described as almost purring, possibly indicating the presence of large animals or vehicles."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-07580d38adc683ab61ef1dfa9a6f1ef8</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TENT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Tent is the shelter where the narrator is sleeping, located on a wooded bluff overlooking the Tarangire River."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-07580d38adc683ab61ef1dfa9a6f1ef8</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 48}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WOODED BLUFF&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ENVIRONMENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Wooded Bluff is the location of the tent, providing a natural barrier and view of the Tarangire River."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-07580d38adc683ab61ef1dfa9a6f1ef8</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 48}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TARANGIRE NATIONAL PARK&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Tarangire National Park is the broader location where the narrator is conducting research, known for its wildlife and rivers."&lt;SEP&gt;"Tarangire National Park is the location where the encounter with the elephants takes place, known for its wildlife and natural environment."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e063ce2c2c82cab519e59545636390db&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-07580d38adc683ab61ef1dfa9a6f1ef8</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 48}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;I&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"I is the narrator of the story, experiencing the encounter with the elephants and describing the events in detail."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e063ce2c2c82cab519e59545636390db</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 47}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;JAMIE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Jamie is the narrator's wife, who wakes up during the encounter with the elephants."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e063ce2c2c82cab519e59545636390db</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 47}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FAMILY OF ELEPHANTS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Family of Elephants refers to a group of elephants that move together, browsing on trees and shrubs, and are not afraid of humans or natural predators."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e063ce2c2c82cab519e59545636390db</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 47}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BULL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Bull is a male elephant in the family, described as huge and towering, with giant ears and strong tusks."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e063ce2c2c82cab519e59545636390db</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 47}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TENTS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Tents are structures where the individuals seek refuge from the elephant."&lt;SEP&gt;"Tents are the temporary shelters where the narrator and Jamie are resting, providing protection from the elements and the elephants."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e063ce2c2c82cab519e59545636390db&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9fa546cd3293c9b8d7663bb92b9e876e</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 45}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;THICKET&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Thicket is the dense vegetation that the elephants bulldoze through, indicating the type of terrain they navigate."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e063ce2c2c82cab519e59545636390db</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 47}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RIVERBED&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Riverbed is the source of water for the elephants, where they come to drink after browsing on trees and shrubs."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e063ce2c2c82cab519e59545636390db</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 47}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PAPARAZZI&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Paparazzi are present around the area, observing the scene but not directly interacting with the elephant."&lt;SEP&gt;"Paparazzi refers to the people taking photos of the elephants, symbolized by the narrator and others peering around the corners of the tents."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e063ce2c2c82cab519e59545636390db&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9fa546cd3293c9b8d7663bb92b9e876e</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 45}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TUSKS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Tusks are elongated incisor teeth found in elephants, used for digging, stripping bark, and defense."&lt;SEP&gt;"Tusks are the elongated incisors of the elephants, described as strong and forklift-like, used for bulldozing through thickets."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e063ce2c2c82cab519e59545636390db&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-116b7be2fde255bf1bbeef908b472818</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 45}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BRANCHES AND TRUNKS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Branches and trunks are the parts of the trees and shrubs that the elephants browse on, shown to be splintering as the elephants move."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e063ce2c2c82cab519e59545636390db</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 47}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CANVAS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"MATERIAL"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Canvas is the material of the tents, described as thin and separating the resting humans from the approaching elephants."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e063ce2c2c82cab519e59545636390db</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 47}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NOISE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Noise is the sound that alerts the narrator and Jamie to the presence of the elephants, causing them to step outside."&lt;SEP&gt;"Noise is the trigger that causes the elephant to react and spook."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e063ce2c2c82cab519e59545636390db&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9fa546cd3293c9b8d7663bb92b9e876e</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 46}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ELEPHANT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Elephant is a large animal that appears to be spooked by noise and exhibits behavior such as trumpeting and moving towards people."&lt;SEP&gt;"Elephant is used as an example of a large animal, weighing about four million grams."&lt;SEP&gt;"Elephants are large mammals known for their long trunks, tusks, and social behavior, with a lifespan of up to 70 years and the ability to reproduce from age 30 to 90."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9fa546cd3293c9b8d7663bb92b9e876e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-116b7be2fde255bf1bbeef908b472818&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-feb346664b4d17cc7509908b0f3a47ec</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 45}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;AMYGDALA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Amygdala is a part of the brain that detects danger and triggers a fight-or-flight response."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9fa546cd3293c9b8d7663bb92b9e876e</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 26}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HYPOTHALAMUS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Hypothalamus is a command center in the brain that receives signals from the amygdala and initiates responses to perceived danger."&lt;SEP&gt;"The hypothalamus sends a chemical signal, corticotropin-releasing factor (CRF), to the pituitary gland to trigger the release of adrenocorticotropic hormone (ACTH)."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9fa546cd3293c9b8d7663bb92b9e876e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93bc63283f93b5a59465f5c505cc5ad3</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 26}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ADRENAL GLANDS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Adrenal Glands are organs that release adrenaline in response to perceived danger."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9fa546cd3293c9b8d7663bb92b9e876e</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 27}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HEART&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Heart is an organ that increases its beating rate in response to adrenaline."&lt;SEP&gt;"The heart is a muscular organ that pumps blood throughout the body, supplying oxygen and nutrients to tissues."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9fa546cd3293c9b8d7663bb92b9e876e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-116b7be2fde255bf1bbeef908b472818</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 27}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LUNGS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Lungs are organs responsible for breathing, containing alveoli for gas exchange and expanding to increase air pressure."&lt;SEP&gt;"Lungs are organs responsible for gas exchange and breathing, expanding and contracting to facilitate inhalation and exhalation."&lt;SEP&gt;"Lungs are organs that increase their breathing rate in response to adrenaline."&lt;SEP&gt;"Lungs are the primary organs of the respiratory system, responsible for gas exchange between the air and the blood."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9fa546cd3293c9b8d7663bb92b9e876e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-758eb501fb5470d3f4e2fe61badac423&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3fb90ae6bf97fbc21cb066ced098ee6c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-116b7be2fde255bf1bbeef908b472818</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 27}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SKELETAL MUSCLES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Skeletal Muscles are organs that increase their contraction in response to adrenaline."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9fa546cd3293c9b8d7663bb92b9e876e</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 27}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LIVER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Liver is an organ that releases stored sugar for energy in response to adrenaline."&lt;SEP&gt;"The liver is a large organ that performs many functions, including detoxification, protein synthesis, and the production of bile."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9fa546cd3293c9b8d7663bb92b9e876e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-116b7be2fde255bf1bbeef908b472818</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 27}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SMOOTH MUSCLES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Smooth Muscles are organs that may relax or contract in response to adrenaline."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9fa546cd3293c9b8d7663bb92b9e876e</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 27}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INDIVIDUALS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Individuals refer to the people present in the scene, including the narrator and others who are not specifically named."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9fa546cd3293c9b8d7663bb92b9e876e</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 46}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NEURONS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Neurons are the cells in the brain that transmit signals and are involved in the fight-or-flight response."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9fa546cd3293c9b8d7663bb92b9e876e</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 27}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BLOODSTREAM&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Bloodstream is the network through which hormones travel to various organs."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9fa546cd3293c9b8d7663bb92b9e876e</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 27}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;THOUGHT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Thought is the mental process of the narrator trying to form a response to the situation."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9fa546cd3293c9b8d7663bb92b9e876e</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 46}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PRIMITIVE PART OF BRAIN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Primitive Part of Brain refers to the amygdala, which is responsible for detecting danger."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9fa546cd3293c9b8d7663bb92b9e876e</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 46}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;KEY ORGANS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Key Organs include the heart, lungs, skeletal muscles, liver, and smooth muscles, which are activated during the fight-or-flight response."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9fa546cd3293c9b8d7663bb92b9e876e</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 46}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MY HEART&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGAN"</data>
  <data key="d1">"My heart is responsible for beating faster to increase blood flow and meet the body's increased demand for oxygen and nutrients during stress responses."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-93bc63283f93b5a59465f5c505cc5ad3</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 26}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MY LUNGS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGAN"</data>
  <data key="d1">"My lungs open up airways and increase breathing rate to provide more oxygen to the body during stress responses."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-93bc63283f93b5a59465f5c505cc5ad3</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 26}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MY SKELETAL MUSCLES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGAN"</data>
  <data key="d1">"My skeletal muscles increase their contraction to prepare the body for physical exertion or fight-or-flight responses."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-93bc63283f93b5a59465f5c505cc5ad3</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 26}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MY LIVER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGAN"</data>
  <data key="d1">"My liver releases stored sugar for a quick supply of energy during stress responses."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-93bc63283f93b5a59465f5c505cc5ad3</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 26}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SMOOTH MUSCLE CELLS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGAN"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Smooth muscle cells throughout my body cause blood vessels to constrict, skin hairs to stand on end, and blood to shunt away from the skin, intestine, and kidneys during stress responses."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-93bc63283f93b5a59465f5c505cc5ad3</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 26}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PITUITARY GLAND&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGAN"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The pituitary gland, upon receiving the chemical signal from the hypothalamus, releases adrenocorticotropic hormone (ACTH) that travels to another part of the adrenal g"&lt;SEP&gt;"The pituitary gland, upon receiving the chemical signal from the hypothalamus, releases adrenocorticotropic hormone (ACTH) that travels to the adrenal gland."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-93bc63283f93b5a59465f5c505cc5ad3</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 26}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ADRENAL GLAND&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGAN"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The adrenal gland, upon receiving adrenocorticotropic hormone (ACTH), releases cortisol and adrenaline, hormones that prepare the body for stress responses."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-93bc63283f93b5a59465f5c505cc5ad3</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 3}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 26}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CORTICOTROPIC RELEASING FACTOR (CRF)&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CHEMICAL"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Corticotropic releasing factor (CRF) is a hormone released by the hypothalamus that triggers the pituitary gland to release adrenocorticotropic hormone (ACTH)."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-93bc63283f93b5a59465f5c505cc5ad3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ADRENOCORTICOTROPIC HORMONE (ACTH)&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CHEMICAL"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Adrenocorticotropic hormone (ACTH) is a hormone released by the pituitary gland that triggers the adrenal gland to release cortisol and adrenaline."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-93bc63283f93b5a59465f5c505cc5ad3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CORTISOL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CHEMICAL"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Cortisol is a hormone released by the adrenal gland in response to stress, helping to regulate metabolism, immune response, and blood pressure."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-93bc63283f93b5a59465f5c505cc5ad3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ADRENALINE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CHEMICAL"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Adrenaline is a hormone released by the adrenal gland in response to stress, increasing heart rate, blood pressure, and blood glucose levels to prepare the body for immediate action."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-93bc63283f93b5a59465f5c505cc5ad3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VOCAL INTENSITY&quot;">
