  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Subsidiaries are affiliated companies owned or controlled by the Company."&lt;SEP&gt;"Subsidiaries are affiliated companies under the same corporate umbrella as the main Company, also involved in selling Products and complying with regulations."&lt;SEP&gt;"Subsidiaries are affiliated organizations under The Company that also comply with labor, employment, and environmental laws."&lt;SEP&gt;"Subsidiaries are companies that are wholly owned or controlled by the Company."&lt;SEP&gt;"Subsidiaries are owned by the Company and operate under its management."&lt;SEP&gt;"Subsidiaries are subsidiaries of the Supporting Lenders, but specific names or details are not provided."&lt;SEP&gt;"Subsidiaries are subsidiary companies of the Parties, which are involved in the transactions and must provide information."&lt;SEP&gt;"Subsidiaries are subsidiary companies owned or controlled by the main company, which also handle intellectual property and confidentiality."&lt;SEP&gt;"Subsidiaries are subsidiary companies under the main entity, sharing the same intellectual property rights."&lt;SEP&gt;"Subsidiaries are subsidiary organizations under the Company, also subject to tax-related requirements and actions."&lt;SEP&gt;"Subsidiaries are subsidiary organizations under the Company, also subject to the same compliance and warranty requirements."&lt;SEP&gt;"Subsidiaries are subsidiary organizations under the Company, which also have obligations related to severance pay and other plans."&lt;SEP&gt;"Subsidiaries refer to companies that are controlled by the main Company, often through ownership or management."&lt;SEP&gt;"Subsidiaries refer to the subsidiary companies of the main company, which collectively own the Company Intellectual Property."</data>
