  <data key="d2">chunk-22412b45b094ae4cf10a2ee87add10b3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WRITTEN NOTICE OF TERMINATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"NOTIFICATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Written notice of termination is a formal notification given to an employee before their employment is terminated."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-22412b45b094ae4cf10a2ee87add10b3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SECTION 7.1(B)(XIX)&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"SECTION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Section 7.1(b)(xix) refers to a specific section in the Company Disclosure Letter that lists officers who received written notice of termination prior to the date of the agreement."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-22412b45b094ae4cf10a2ee87add10b3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;OFFICER WHO WAS PROVIDED WITH WRITTEN NOTICE OF TERMINATION PRIOR TO THE DATE OF THIS AGREEMENT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"An officer who was provided with written notice of termination prior to the date of the agreement is an individual whose employment termination was formally notified before the agreement was signed."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-22412b45b094ae4cf10a2ee87add10b3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PLANS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Plans refer to specific strategies or initiatives that the Company may develop and implement."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-22412b45b094ae4cf10a2ee87add10b3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HOMEMADE HIVE STAND&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"homemade hive stand is a custom-built structure designed to support beehives, offering stability and space for beekeeping activities."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0888a4c0f0cc346c6d0753813ecc9e49</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TREATED 2-BY-4S OR 2-BY-6S&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"MATERIAL"</data>
  <data key="d1">"treated 2-by-4s or 2-by-6s are types of lumber used in constructing the stand, known for their durability and resistance to rot."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0888a4c0f0cc346c6d0753813ecc9e49</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COMMERCIALLY-AVAILABLE STANDS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"commercially-available stands are pre-made hive stands sold in equipment catalogs, typically narrower and less stable compared to homemade stands."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0888a4c0f0cc346c6d0753813ecc9e49</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HIVE BODIES OR SUPERS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EQUIPMENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"hive bodies or supers are components of a beehive used to store honey and brood, requiring separation tools for maintenance."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0888a4c0f0cc346c6d0753813ecc9e49</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HIVE TOOL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A Hive Tool is a tool used in beekeeping to open hives and remove frames without damaging the hive or adjacent frames."&lt;SEP&gt;"hive tool is a specialized tool used to separate hive bodies or supers, essential for beekeeping tasks."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0b574feb85a5c2c80686afdf892d9573&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0888a4c0f0cc346c6d0753813ecc9e49</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;OLD SCREWDRIVER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EQUIPMENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"old screwdriver is mentioned as a potential alternative to a hive tool, but it can cause severe damage to the hives."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0888a4c0f0cc346c6d0753813ecc9e49</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BEEHIVE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"beehive is the structure where bees live and produce honey, requiring proper tools and stands for maintenance."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0888a4c0f0cc346c6d0753813ecc9e49</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FRAME LIFTER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A Frame Lifter is a specialized tool used in beekeeping to remove frames from hives without damaging adjacent frames or the hive body."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0b574feb85a5c2c80686afdf892d9573</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SMOKER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A Smoker is a tool used in beekeeping to calm and soothe bees, making hive work easier for the beekeeper."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0b574feb85a5c2c80686afdf892d9573</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PROTECTIVE GEAR&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EQUIPMENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Protective Gear is equipment worn by beekeepers to protect themselves from bee stings during hive work."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0b574feb85a5c2c80686afdf892d9573</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SUPERS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Supers are additional boxes added to a hive to provide more space for the bees to store honey and raise brood."&lt;SEP&gt;"Supers are additional boxes added to the hive to provide space for the colony, often used to prevent congestion and reduce swarming impulses."&lt;SEP&gt;"Supers are additional boxes added to the hive to provide space for the colony, often used to relieve congestion without paying close attention to the overall needs of the colony."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0b574feb85a5c2c80686afdf892d9573&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-41c3aaf395c33844b42f907bc25d40ac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WEATHER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Weather affects the behavior and activity levels of bees, influencing their foraging and interaction with humans."&lt;SEP&gt;"Weather refers to the atmospheric conditions affecting the hive, such as temperature and humidity."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0b574feb85a5c2c80686afdf892d9573&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9c3204e91cca2a19fc99c297c42ffa77</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DECAY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Decay is the process of deterioration or rotting of the hive structure due to environmental factors."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0b574feb85a5c2c80686afdf892d9573</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TOOLBOX&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EQUIPMENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A Toolbox is a storage container for various tools, including hive tools and smokers."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0b574feb85a5c2c80686afdf892d9573</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BOARDMAN FEEDER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Boardman Feeder is a specific type of feeder used in beekeeping, often paired with a quart jar or a 5-pound honey jar."&lt;SEP&gt;"Boardman Feeder is a type of feeder used in beekeeping, typically smaller and not suitable for new colonies in the spring due to its size and exposure to cold."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d8206d1a6432719f1f3ae2c3737308ac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;4-BY-7-INCH SMOKER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"4-by-7-inch Smoker is a smaller size of smoker used for beekeeping, suitable for one or two hives."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d8206d1a6432719f1f3ae2c3737308ac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;4-BY-10-INCH SMOKER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"4-by-10-inch Smoker is a larger size of smoker used for beekeeping, more durable and better suited for multiple hives."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d8206d1a6432719f1f3ae2c3737308ac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;STAINLESS STEEL SMOKER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Stainless Steel Smoker is a durable and expensive type of smoker used in beekeeping, preferred over those made of galvanized metal or tinplate."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d8206d1a6432719f1f3ae2c3737308ac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GALVANIZED METAL SMOKER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Galvanized Metal Smoker is a type of smoker used in beekeeping, less durable and cheaper than stainless steel smokers."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d8206d1a6432719f1f3ae2c3737308ac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TINPLATE SMOKER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Tinplate Smoker is a type of smoker used in beekeeping, less durable and cheaper than stainless steel smokers."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d8206d1a6432719f1f3ae2c3737308ac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FEEDER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A feeder is a device used to provide food to bees, typically placed near the hive to ensure they have access to nourishment."&lt;SEP&gt;"Feeder is a device used in beekeeping to provide food to bees, such as sugar syrup or honey."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d8206d1a6432719f1f3ae2c3737308ac&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9c3204e91cca2a19fc99c297c42ffa77</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GALLON GLASS JAR&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Gallon Glass Jar is a container used in beekeeping for feeding bees, placed on the inner cover for easy access."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d8206d1a6432719f1f3ae2c3737308ac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INNER COVER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Inner Cover is a part of the beehive structure, used to place feeding containers for easy access by bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d8206d1a6432719f1f3ae2c3737308ac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SUGAR SYRUP&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Sugar Syrup is a type of food provided to bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d8206d1a6432719f1f3ae2c3737308ac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CLUSTER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Cluster is the group of bees that stay together."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d8206d1a6432719f1f3ae2c3737308ac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BEEKEEPING EQUIPMENT CATALOGS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Beekeeping Equipment Catalogs are sources where beginner outfits and feeders are sold."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d8206d1a6432719f1f3ae2c3737308ac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PAGES 84 AND 88&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Pages 84 and 88 are specific pages in a guide or manual."&lt;SEP&gt;"Pages 84 and 88 contain detailed descriptions of methods for using gallon glass jars as feeders in beekeeping."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d8206d1a6432719f1f3ae2c3737308ac&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9c3204e91cca2a19fc99c297c42ffa77</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BEEHIVE STRUCTURE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Beehive Structure is the overall structure of the hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d8206d1a6432719f1f3ae2c3737308ac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BEEKEEPING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Beekeeping is the practice of keeping honeybees, and its historical context is discussed in the text."&lt;SEP&gt;"Beekeeping is the practice of keeping honeybees, and its historical context is discussed in the text.")&lt;SEP&gt;"Beekeeping is the practice of managing and maintaining bee colonies."&lt;SEP&gt;"Beekeeping is the practice of managing beehives and bees."&lt;SEP&gt;"Beekeeping refers to the practice of managing and utilizing bees, particularly for honey production, which was more about exploiting bees rather than keeping them in early times."&lt;SEP&gt;"Beekeeping refers to the practice of managing and utilizing honeybee colonies, which has a rich historical background spanning multiple eras."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d84a5beb18cbfd1e9fa66937ebb5293b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e12a53f3b6ece3d5992379cab9e9f17b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d8206d1a6432719f1f3ae2c3737308ac&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0098193a3d104a7324b88d9086bac046&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e52c63f43f0f8ca942825a1048d86e1e</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BEE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Bee is the individual insect managed by beekeepers."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bee refers to a social insect belonging to the family Apidae, known for pollination and honey production."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d8206d1a6432719f1f3ae2c3737308ac&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c680a6b8b3e81c2296be9f38f10110eb</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GALVANIZED METAL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"MATERIAL"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Galvanized Metal is a type of metal used in smokers."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d8206d1a6432719f1f3ae2c3737308ac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TINPLATE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"MATERIAL"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Tinplate is another type of metal used in smokers."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d8206d1a6432719f1f3ae2c3737308ac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;STAINLESS STEEL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"MATERIAL"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Stainless Steel is a durable material used in smokers."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d8206d1a6432719f1f3ae2c3737308ac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VEIL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A veil is a protective piece of clothing worn during beekeeping to shield the face from bee stings."&lt;SEP&gt;"Veil is a piece of protective clothing worn by Beekeepers to cover their faces, reducing the risk of bee stings."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e3273db468e99ebc0efe06440d174a65&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9c3204e91cca2a19fc99c297c42ffa77</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HELMET&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A helmet is a protective piece of clothing worn during beekeeping to shield the head from bee stings."&lt;SEP&gt;"Helmet is a protective headgear worn by Beekeepers to shield their heads from bee stings."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e3273db468e99ebc0efe06440d174a65&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9c3204e91cca2a19fc99c297c42ffa77</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BEEKEEPING ATTIRE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Beekeeping attire includes protective clothing such as veils and helmets to ensure safety while handling bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9c3204e91cca2a19fc99c297c42ffa77</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NECTAR FLOWS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Nectar flows refer to periods when bees collect large amounts of nectar, which is influenced by weather conditions."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9c3204e91cca2a19fc99c297c42ffa77</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FORAGING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ACTIVITY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Foraging is the process by which bees collect nectar and pollen, which is heavily influenced by weather conditions."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9c3204e91cca2a19fc99c297c42ffa77</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GALLON GLASS JARS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Gallon glass jars are used as feeders in beekeeping, often obtained from restaurants or school cafeterias."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9c3204e91cca2a19fc99c297c42ffa77</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PLASTIC PAILS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Plastic pails are used as feeders in beekeeping and are available through regular beekeeping equipment sources."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9c3204e91cca2a19fc99c297c42ffa77</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COMMERCIAL MAYONNAISE OR PICKLES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PRODUCT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Commercial mayonnaise or pickles are products that can be repurposed as feeders after being emptied."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9c3204e91cca2a19fc99c297c42ffa77</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RESTAURANTS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Restaurants are sources of empty gallon glass jars that can be repurposed as feeders in beekeeping."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9c3204e91cca2a19fc99c297c42ffa77</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SCHOOL CAFETERIAS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"School cafeterias are sources of empty gallon glass jars that can be repurposed as feeders in beekeeping."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9c3204e91cca2a19fc99c297c42ffa77</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;REGULAR BEEKEEPING EQUIPMENT SOURCES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Regular beekeeping equipment sources are places where plastic pails designed for feeder use can be purchased."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9c3204e91cca2a19fc99c297c42ffa77</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NECTAR FLOW&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Nectar Flow is a period when bees are actively collecting nectar, making them less concerned with minor disturbances."&lt;SEP&gt;"Nectar flow refers to periods when flowers are blooming and producing nectar, which can trigger swarming."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e3273db468e99ebc0efe06440d174a65&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7744ce257d4323a8eb4027b5dc0cb920</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CLOUDY DAY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Cloudy Day is a weather condition that typically results in less nectar flow, affecting the bees' behavior."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e3273db468e99ebc0efe06440d174a65</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HOT DAY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Hot Day is a weather condition that causes bees to stop foraging and gather around the hive, making them more likely to be disturbed."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e3273db468e99ebc0efe06440d174a65</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BEE SUIT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Bee Suit is a full-body protective garment worn by Beekeepers to minimize exposure to bees."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bee Suit is a protective garment designed to shield the wearer from bee stings during hive inspections."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e3273db468e99ebc0efe06440d174a65&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e537830582229543208b23bd5f379d24</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GLOVES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Gloves are protective hand coverings worn by Beekeepers to prevent bee stings."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e3273db468e99ebc0efe06440d174a65</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MINOR DISTURBANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Minor Disturbance is a term used to describe situations that do not significantly affect the bees when they are busy with nectar collection."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e3273db468e99ebc0efe06440d174a65</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FORAGERS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Foragers are experienced bees that leave the hive to collect nectar and pollen, and their venom glands are fully functional."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e3273db468e99ebc0efe06440d174a65</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VENOM GLANDS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Venom Glands are specialized structures in bees that produce venom used for defense."&lt;SEP&gt;"Venom Glands control the inclination and ability to sting, which develop over time."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-eabc0181d0cf67701c935fe928f272cb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e3273db468e99ebc0efe06440d174a65</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SUMMER OUTING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Summer Outing is a casual activity that some Beekeepers engage in while managing bees, often without heavy protective gear."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e3273db468e99ebc0efe06440d174a65</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FACE VULNERABILITY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Face Vulnerability is the increased risk of bee stings to the face area, which is a primary target for bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e3273db468e99ebc0efe06440d174a65</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DARK COLORS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Dark Colors refer to clothing colors that bees tend to react adversely to, such as black, navy, or dark brown."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e537830582229543208b23bd5f379d24</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WOOLLY OR HAIRY FABRICS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Woolly or Hairy Fabrics are materials that bees may react adversely to, as they can make the wearer resemble an animal."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e537830582229543208b23bd5f379d24</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ANIMAL RESEMBLANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Animal Resemblance refers to the similarity of clothing to animal fur or skin, which can trigger adverse reactions from bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e537830582229543208b23bd5f379d24</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SKUNK&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ANIMAL"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Skunk is an animal whose scent can trigger adverse reactions from bees, making dark colors more dangerous when near skunks."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e537830582229543208b23bd5f379d24</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BEAR&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ANIMAL"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Bear is an animal whose scent can trigger adverse reactions from bees, making dark colors more dangerous when near bears."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e537830582229543208b23bd5f379d24</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PERFUME&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Perfume is a fragrance applied to the skin or hair, advised against due to its attractiveness to bees."&lt;SEP&gt;"Perfume is a fragrance that can be detected by bees and may trigger adverse reactions, making it advisable to avoid wearing it around bees."&lt;SEP&gt;"Perfume is mentioned as something to avoid."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a3359e9ea7553a8920a2aaf90b589a9d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e537830582229543208b23bd5f379d24</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HAIR SPRAY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Hair Spray is a product that can leave a detectable odor, which may trigger adverse reactions from bees, making it advisable to avoid using it around bees."&lt;SEP&gt;"Hair Spray is mentioned as something to avoid."&lt;SEP&gt;"Hair spray is a fragrance applied to hair, advised against due to its attractiveness to bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a3359e9ea7553a8920a2aaf90b589a9d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e537830582229543208b23bd5f379d24</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;AFTER-SHAVE LOTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"After-Shave Lotion is a product that can leave a detectable odor, which may trigger adverse reactions from bees, making it advisable to avoid using it around bees."&lt;SEP&gt;"After-Shave Lotion is mentioned as something to avoid."&lt;SEP&gt;"After-shave lotion is a fragrance applied to the skin after shaving, advised against due to its attractiveness to bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a3359e9ea7553a8920a2aaf90b589a9d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e537830582229543208b23bd5f379d24</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PANTS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Pants are mentioned in relation to securing pant cuffs."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e537830582229543208b23bd5f379d24</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SOCKS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Socks are items of clothing worn on the feet, mentioned as a primary target for bees due to their color and scent."&lt;SEP&gt;"Socks are mentioned in relation to color and bee targets."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a3359e9ea7553a8920a2aaf90b589a9d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e537830582229543208b23bd5f379d24</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HANDS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"BODY PART"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Hands are used to work the hive and can be targets for bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e537830582229543208b23bd5f379d24</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WHITE SOCKS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"White Socks are specifically mentioned as better than dark ones."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e537830582229543208b23bd5f379d24</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DARK SOCKS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Dark Socks are mentioned as becoming a primary target if bees are upset."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e537830582229543208b23bd5f379d24</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RED&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"COLOR"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Red is a color that appears black to bees, making it a factor in avoiding bee attraction."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a3359e9ea7553a8920a2aaf90b589a9d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GASOLINE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Gasoline is a petroleum product that may leave a residual odor offensive to bees, affecting their behavior."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a3359e9ea7553a8920a2aaf90b589a9d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BANANA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Banana is a fruit whose odor is associated with the alarm pheromone of bees, according to an old beekeeper's tale."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a3359e9ea7553a8920a2aaf90b589a9d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CLOTHING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Clothing can attract bees if it carries scents such as perfume, hair spray, or after-shave lotion."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a3359e9ea7553a8920a2aaf90b589a9d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HEAD&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"BODY PART"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Head is the part of the body where bees may investigate, bump, and bang around, causing apprehension."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a3359e9ea7553a8920a2aaf90b589a9d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ALARM ODOR&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Alarm odor is the scent released by bees when they sting, which can be mistaken for the smell of bananas."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a3359e9ea7553a8920a2aaf90b589a9d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ENTRANCE BOARD&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Entrance board is a part of a hive where bees enter and exit, often used by beekeepers for observation."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a3359e9ea7553a8920a2aaf90b589a9d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DRONE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Drone is a type of bee, male and non-reproductive, often found in hives."&lt;SEP&gt;"Drone refers to a specific type of bee that plays a crucial role in the colony's reproduction and survival, undergoing a maturation process and performing various tasks."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a3359e9ea7553a8920a2aaf90b589a9d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-53bded4e4e03e96ec81a62d617d36cdd</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LARVA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"LIFE STAGE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Larva is the early life stage of a bee, which is shorter for workers compared to the queen."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a3359e9ea7553a8920a2aaf90b589a9d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WORKER BEE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Worker Bee is a caste within the bee colony responsible for various tasks such as eating, wandering about the brood nest, resting, and completing muscular and glandular development."&lt;SEP&gt;"Worker Bee is a type of bee responsible for various tasks within the hive, such as producing honey and caring for the young."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a4d7e57c2743de34cc14320da6e7fe95&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7251f3651e5cd421ae992f26de8129b2</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;QUEEN BEE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Queen Bee is a caste within the bee colony with a larger cell size for her longer body, needing to grow into her job after emergence, making orientation and mating flights, and eventually laying eggs."&lt;SEP&gt;"Queen Bee is responsible for reducing her rate of egg laying before the swarm event."&lt;SEP&gt;"Queen Bee is the female reproductive member of the hive, responsible for laying eggs and maintaining the social structure of the colony."&lt;SEP&gt;"Queen Bee is the reproductive female in the hive responsible for laying eggs, but her actions are influenced by worker bees rather than being in charge."&lt;SEP&gt;"Queen bee is the female reproductive member of the hive, responsible for laying eggs."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-7251f3651e5cd421ae992f26de8129b2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7744ce257d4323a8eb4027b5dc0cb920&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e52c63f43f0f8ca942825a1048d86e1e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-54cbc98c2355f1563efcd1e13da95f19&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a4d7e57c2743de34cc14320da6e7fe95</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DRONE BEE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Drone Bee is a caste within the bee colony similar to workers in brood stage, making orientation flights, and taking about 2 weeks for reproductive organs to mature."&lt;SEP&gt;"Drone Bee is a male bee whose primary role is to mate with the queen, contributing to the genetic diversity of the colony."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a4d7e57c2743de34cc14320da6e7fe95&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7251f3651e5cd421ae992f26de8129b2</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;EMERGENCE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Emergence is the process by which the queen bee emerges from her cell, marking the beginning of her role as a queen."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-a4d7e57c2743de34cc14320da6e7fe95</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WORKER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Worker bees are the non-reproductive females of the colony, responsible for various tasks such as foraging, nursing, and defending the hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-53bded4e4e03e96ec81a62d617d36cdd</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BROOD AREA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Brood Area is a specific region within the hive where the queen lays her eggs and the young bees develop."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-53bded4e4e03e96ec81a62d617d36cdd</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ACTIVE SEASON&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Active Season is the period during which the colony is most active, involving tasks such as foraging, mating, and brood rearing."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Active Season is a period during which workers raise drones and forage, leading to resource expenditure."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-eabc0181d0cf67701c935fe928f272cb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-53bded4e4e03e96ec81a62d617d36cdd</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DRONE'S REPRODUCTIVE ORGANS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Drone's Reproductive Organs refer to the organs that mature over 2 weeks, allowing the Drone to perform its reproductive function."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-53bded4e4e03e96ec81a62d617d36cdd</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ORIENTATION FLIGHTS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Orientation Flights are performed by Dr..."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-53bded4e4e03e96ec81a62d617d36cdd</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;QUEEN'S EGGS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Queen's Eggs are laid by the Queen and develop into Young Bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-53bded4e4e03e96ec81a62d617d36cdd</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;YOUNG BEES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Young Bees are the developing offspring of the Queen's Eggs."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-53bded4e4e03e96ec81a62d617d36cdd</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MATING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Mating is the process where a Drone finds a Queen and mates, either ending its life or continuing to live."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-53bded4e4e03e96ec81a62d617d36cdd</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;OLD AGE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Old Age is the natural end of a Drone's life if it does not mate."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-53bded4e4e03e96ec81a62d617d36cdd</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;REMAINING DRONES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Remaining Drones are those left after the active season ends."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-53bded4e4e03e96ec81a62d617d36cdd</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WINTER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Winter is a season when temperatures drop, affecting the activity levels and survival rates of bees."&lt;SEP&gt;"Winter is the time when Drones are not allowed to survive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-53bded4e4e03e96ec81a62d617d36cdd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7744ce257d4323a8eb4027b5dc0cb920</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CELLS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Cells are individual units within the comb where bees store honey and lay eggs."&lt;SEP&gt;"Cells are locations where eggs are laid in the hive.")&lt;SEP&gt;"Cells are the structures where Drones are raised."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-7251f3651e5cd421ae992f26de8129b2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-53bded4e4e03e96ec81a62d617d36cdd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-573b4d1e9d950dca730f99b82578a0ac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DRONES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Drones are believed to spread sperm over eggs laid in cells within the hive.")&lt;SEP&gt;"Drones are male bees whose primary role is to mate with the queen and contribute to genetic diversity."&lt;SEP&gt;"Drones are necessary for the well-being of the colony and are raised by workers during the active season, leading to resource expenditure."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-eabc0181d0cf67701c935fe928f272cb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7251f3651e5cd421ae992f26de8129b2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-573b4d1e9d950dca730f99b82578a0ac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WORKERS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Workers are responsible for raising drones and foraging, and they go to great lengths to replace drones during the active season."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-eabc0181d0cf67701c935fe928f272cb</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HONEY BEES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Honey bees are insects that react to specific stimuli based on their genetic programming and physiological development."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-eabc0181d0cf67701c935fe928f272cb</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COLONY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A Colony is a group of honey bees living together, dependent on drones and workers for its survival."&lt;SEP&gt;"Colony is a group of bees that is preparing to swarm."&lt;SEP&gt;"Colony refers to a group of bees living together in a hive, managed by a beekeeper."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-eabc0181d0cf67701c935fe928f272cb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e52c63f43f0f8ca942825a1048d86e1e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7744ce257d4323a8eb4027b5dc0cb920</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MUSCULAR DEVELOPMENT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Muscular Development controls flight in bees and is part of their physiological development."&lt;SEP&gt;"Muscular development pertains to the growth and maturation of muscles, particularly important for flight in bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-eabc0181d0cf67701c935fe928f272cb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c680a6b8b3e81c2296be9f38f10110eb</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NERVOUS AND SENSORY SYSTEMS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Nervous and sensory systems involve the detection of stimuli and coordination of actions, crucial for a bee's survival."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Nervous and Sensory Systems allow bees to detect stimuli and are part of their physiological development."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-eabc0181d0cf67701c935fe928f272cb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c680a6b8b3e81c2296be9f38f10110eb</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GENETIC PROGRAMMING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Genetic Programming dictates the behavior and reactions of bees from birth."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-eabc0181d0cf67701c935fe928f272cb</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;STIMULI&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Stimuli are specific triggers that cause bees to react based on their physiological development."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-eabc0181d0cf67701c935fe928f272cb</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FLIGHT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Flight is controlled by muscular development and is essential for bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-eabc0181d0cf67701c935fe928f272cb</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DETECTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Detection of stimuli is facilitated by the nervous and sensory systems and is crucial for bees' survival."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-eabc0181d0cf67701c935fe928f272cb</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INCLINATION TO STING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The Inclination to Sting develops over time and is tied to the maturation of the bee's venom glands."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-eabc0181d0cf67701c935fe928f272cb</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MATURATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Maturation of the bee's venom glands is a key factor in the development of the inclination to sting."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-eabc0181d0cf67701c935fe928f272cb</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RESOURCE EXPENDITURE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Resource Expenditure occurs during the active season as workers raise drones and forage."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-eabc0181d0cf67701c935fe928f272cb</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PHYSIOLOGICAL DEVELOPMENT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Physiological Development continues over at least the first half of a bee's adult life and affects various behaviors and abilities."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-eabc0181d0cf67701c935fe928f272cb</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GLANDULAR DEVELOPMENT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Glandular development allows for the secretion of substances such as wax and venom, essential for hive maintenance and defense."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c680a6b8b3e81c2296be9f38f10110eb</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VOCAL FOLDS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Vocal Folds are structures in the larynx that vibrate to produce sound, and are set into vibration by air from the lungs."&lt;SEP&gt;"Vocal Folds are structures in the larynx that vibrate to produce sound, though typically not found in bees."&lt;SEP&gt;"Vocal Folds are structures that run from the thyroid cartilage to the arytenoids and are responsible for producing sound through vibration."&lt;SEP&gt;"Vocal Folds, also known as vocal cords, are the primary structures responsible for sound production in the vocal system."&lt;SEP&gt;"Vocal folds are structures in the larynx that vibrate to produce sound, requiring air from the lungs to set them into vibration."&lt;SEP&gt;"Vocal folds are structures in the larynx that vibrate to produce sound, requiring air from the lungs."&lt;SEP&gt;"Vocal folds are structures in the larynx that vibrate to produce sound, though typically not found in bees."&lt;SEP&gt;"Vocal folds, also known as vocal cords, are flaps of tissue located in the larynx that vibrate to produce sound."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1b275cbb65dda44f47ce44df6a2fb9cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dca9303a607f377e06cf6c0a4f271e11&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3fb90ae6bf97fbc21cb066ced098ee6c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7ecb7e98904dcdb0df7a95baf5e657fc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-758eb501fb5470d3f4e2fe61badac423&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c680a6b8b3e81c2296be9f38f10110eb</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 1}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 15}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;THYROID CARTILAGE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Thyroid Cartilage is a specific type of cartilage that plays a crucial role in the structure of the larynx, connecting with other cartilages to form the vocal folds and regulate the glottis."&lt;SEP&gt;"Thyroid Cartilage is the largest of the laryngeal cartilages, shaped like a small shield and connected to the cricoid cartilage."&lt;SEP&gt;"Thyroid cartilage is the largest of the laryngeal cartilages, shaped like a small shield and connected to the cricoid cartilage."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c680a6b8b3e81c2296be9f38f10110eb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7ecb7e98904dcdb0df7a95baf5e657fc</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CRICOID CARTILAGE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Cricoid Cartilage is a ring-shaped cartilage that supports the larynx and connects with the arytenoids to form part of the vocal folds."&lt;SEP&gt;"Cricoid Cartilage is shaped like a signet ring, broad in the back and narrow in the front, connecting to the thyroid cartilage."&lt;SEP&gt;"Cricoid cartilage is shaped like a signet ring, broad in the back and narrow in the front, connecting to the thyroid cartilage."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c680a6b8b3e81c2296be9f38f10110eb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7ecb7e98904dcdb0df7a95baf5e657fc</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ARYTENOIDS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Arytenoids are two cartilages shaped like squashed pyramids that sit atop the cricoid and are involved in the formation of the vocal folds."&lt;SEP&gt;"Arytenoids are two cartilages shaped like squashed pyramids that sit atop the cricoid cartilage."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c680a6b8b3e81c2296be9f38f10110eb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7ecb7e98904dcdb0df7a95baf5e657fc</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 1}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 16}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LARYNGITIS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Laryngitis is a condition that causes inflammation in the vocal folds, leading to difficulty or impossibility in phonation."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c680a6b8b3e81c2296be9f38f10110eb</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;APHONIA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Aphonia is a condition where the vocal folds are tightly coupled, making phonation difficult or impossible due to inflammation."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c680a6b8b3e81c2296be9f38f10110eb</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;EPIGLOTTIS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Epiglottis is a flap located at the top of the larynx that flips backward during swallowing to prevent food and liquid from entering the lungs."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-7ecb7e98904dcdb0df7a95baf5e657fc</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 1}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 16}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GLOTTIS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Glottis is the opening between the vocal folds that can be opened and closed by muscles attached to the various cartilages, controlling the passage of air."&lt;SEP&gt;"Glottis is the part of the throat where the vocal folds are located, crucial for producing sound."&lt;SEP&gt;"Glottis is the space between the vocal folds where sound is produced in the larynx."&lt;SEP&gt;"The glottis is the location within the vocal system where sound production begins, formed by two flaps of tissue known as vocal folds."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6e594c09c6de0c01da248106da72ab77&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1b275cbb65dda44f47ce44df6a2fb9cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7ecb7e98904dcdb0df7a95baf5e657fc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dca9303a607f377e06cf6c0a4f271e11</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 1}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 16}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;THYROARYTENOID MUSCLE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Thyroarytenoid Muscle, also known as the vocalis muscle, connects the thyroid cartilage to the arytenoids and controls the shortening of the vocal folds, lowering pitch."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-7ecb7e98904dcdb0df7a95baf5e657fc</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CRICOTHYROID MUSCLE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Cricothyroid Muscle connects the thyroid cartilage to the cricoid cartilage and controls the elongation of the vocal folds, raising pitch."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-7ecb7e98904dcdb0df7a95baf5e657fc</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MUSCLES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Muscles are responsible for opening and closing the glottis and lengthening and shortening the vocal folds, allowing for pitch control and vocal function."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-7ecb7e98904dcdb0df7a95baf5e657fc</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 1}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 16}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VOCAL FUNCTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Vocal Function refers to the ability to produce sound and control pitch, which is influenced by the structure and movement of the vocal folds and related cartilages."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-7ecb7e98904dcdb0df7a95baf5e657fc</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SOUND PRODUCTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Sound Production is the process of generating sound through the vibration of the vocal folds, which is regulated by the muscles and cartilages of the larynx."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-7ecb7e98904dcdb0df7a95baf5e657fc</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RESONANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Resonance is the amplification of sound within the vocal tract, contributing to the timbre or quality of the voice."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-7ecb7e98904dcdb0df7a95baf5e657fc</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 1}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 19}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VOCAL TRACT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Vocal Tract is the pathway through which sound travels from the larynx to the mouth and nose, affecting the timbre of the voice."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-7ecb7e98904dcdb0df7a95baf5e657fc</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 1}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 19}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LARYNX&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Larynx is the voice box, located in the throat, responsible for producing sound and protecting the airway."&lt;SEP&gt;"Larynx, also known as the voice box or Adam's apple, is a complex structure involved in speech, singing, and protecting the airway."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6e594c09c6de0c01da248106da72ab77&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dca9303a607f377e06cf6c0a4f271e11</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 11}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VOCAL OR GLOTTAL SOUND&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Vocal or glottal sound refers to the sound produced by the glottis, which is complex and contains multiple frequencies."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6e594c09c6de0c01da248106da72ab77</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 10}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FUNDAMENTAL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Fundamental is the lowest frequency within any tone, corresponding to its named pitch in the musical scale."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6e594c09c6de0c01da248106da72ab77</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 10}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;A-440&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A-440 is a specific pitch used for tuning orchestras, with a frequency of 440 vibrations per second or 440 Hertz."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6e594c09c6de0c01da248106da72ab77</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 10}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;OVERTONES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Overtones are additional frequencies above the fundamental in the glottal sound, typically whole number multiples of the fundamental."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6e594c09c6de0c01da248106da72ab77</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 10}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HARMONIC SERIES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Harmonic series is the pattern formed by overtones, which are quieter than the fundamental."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6e594c09c6de0c01da248106da72ab77</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 10}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ORCHESTRA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Orchestra is a group of musicians playing various instruments, often tuning to A-440."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6e594c09c6de0c01da248106da72ab77</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 10}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BUZZ&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Buzz is a sound produced by the glottis, similar to a duck call, which contains the raw material for speech and singing."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6e594c09c6de0c01da248106da72ab77</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 10}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ANNOYING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Annoying describes the nature of the buzz produced by the glottis, which is not pleasant but contains necessary frequencies."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6e594c09c6de0c01da248106da72ab77</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SPEECH&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Speech is the act of producing meaningful sounds using the vocal apparatus, built upon the fundamental and overtones."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6e594c09c6de0c01da248106da72ab77</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 14}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SOUND&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Sound is the physical phenomenon of vibrations that travel through the air and are perceived as noise or speech."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6e594c09c6de0c01da248106da72ab77</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 14}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VIBRATIONS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Vibrations refer to the oscillations that produce sound waves, measured in Hertz."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6e594c09c6de0c01da248106da72ab77</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 14}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HZ&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Hz is the abbreviation for Hertz, the unit of frequency measurement."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6e594c09c6de0c01da248106da72ab77</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 14}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TUNING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Tuning is the process of adjusting the pitch of musical instruments to a standard frequency, such as A-440."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6e594c09c6de0c01da248106da72ab77</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 10}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PITCH&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Pitch is the perceived frequency of a sound, measured in Hertz, and used to describe the highness or lowness of a tone."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-6e594c09c6de0c01da248106da72ab77</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 10}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;AFFILIATES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Affiliates are affiliates of the Supporting Lenders, but specific names or details are not provided."&lt;SEP&gt;"Affiliates are related companies or entities associated with the Company."&lt;SEP&gt;"Affiliates are related companies or entities under the same ownership or control as the Supporting Lenders."&lt;SEP&gt;"Affiliates are related organizations associated with the Company and Supporting Lenders."&lt;SEP&gt;"Affiliates are related organizations or subsidiaries of the Company or Supporting Lenders."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-4399a6044c475cc6817f92d0cda2f1af&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-50c13e3bb8e4150848f52b75b8673473&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dc4be754ab02233d9e6804456be8d754&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0098193a3d104a7324b88d9086bac046&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-52ea1096ae3f4e248ede1dc1be934a73</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 28}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DUE DILIGENCE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Due Diligence refers to the process of conducting an investigation or audit of a company, project, or investment before proceeding with a transaction."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-52ea1096ae3f4e248ede1dc1be934a73</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 21}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 49}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TRANSACTIONS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Transactions refer to specific business activities or agreements that are the subject of the agreement."&lt;SEP&gt;"Transactions refer to specific business activities or agreements that are the subject of the agreement.")&lt;SEP&gt;"Transactions refer to the actions and agreements related to the Restructuring process."&lt;SEP&gt;"Transactions refer to the agreements and actions contemplated by the supporting lenders and the company."&lt;SEP&gt;"Transactions refer to the business activities or agreements between the Company and other parties."&lt;SEP&gt;"Transactions refer to the business activities or agreements that are subject to antitrust laws and require regulatory compliance."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-4399a6044c475cc6817f92d0cda2f1af&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-50c13e3bb8e4150848f52b75b8673473&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0098193a3d104a7324b88d9086bac046&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-52ea1096ae3f4e248ede1dc1be934a73&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e52c63f43f0f8ca942825a1048d86e1e</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 30}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 56}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;REPRESENTATIONS AND WARRANTIES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Representations and Warranties are legal statements made by one party to another regarding the truthfulness and accuracy of certain facts or conditions."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-52ea1096ae3f4e248ede1dc1be934a73</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 20}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INFORMATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Information refers to the data and details provided in connection with the transactions."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-52ea1096ae3f4e248ede1dc1be934a73</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 20}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SECTION 6.1 QUALIFICATION; ORGANIZATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Section 6.1 Qualification; Organization is a specific section within the agreement detailing the qualifications and organizational status of the Supporting Lenders."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ff621339cc48c1d0afec4e0b8efe1d64</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 29}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;JURISDICTIONS THAT RECOGNIZE SUCH CONCEPT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Jurisdictions that recognize such concept refer to legal frameworks where the concepts of 'duly organized', 'validly existing', and 'good standing' are recognized."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ff621339cc48c1d0afec4e0b8efe1d64</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 29}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LEGAL ENTITY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Legal entity refers to an organization that is recognized by law as having its own rights and liabilities, distinct from those of its members or owners."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ff621339cc48c1d0afec4e0b8efe1d64</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 29}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DULY ORGANIZED&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Duly organized refers to the proper formation and registration of a legal entity according to the laws of its jurisdiction of organization."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ff621339cc48c1d0afec4e0b8efe1d64</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 29}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VALIDLY EXISTING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Validly existing refers to a legal entity that has been properly formed and continues to exist without any legal impediments."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ff621339cc48c1d0afec4e0b8efe1d64</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GOOD STANDING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Good standing refers to a legal entity that complies with all legal requirements and obligations, and has no outstanding issues that would affect its legal status."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ff621339cc48c1d0afec4e0b8efe1d64</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 29}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;REQUISITE CORPORATE OR SIMILAR POWER AND AUTHORITY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Requisite corporate or similar power and authority refers to the legal rights and permissions necessary for a legal entity to own, lease, and operate properties and assets, and to conduct business."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ff621339cc48c1d0afec4e0b8efe1d64</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 29}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FOREIGN CORPORATION OR OTHER ENTITY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Foreign corporation or other entity refers to a legal entity that is registered and operates in a jurisdiction other than its jurisdiction of organization."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ff621339cc48c1d0afec4e0b8efe1d64</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 29}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MATERIAL IMPAIRMENT OR MATERIAL DELAY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Material impairment or material delay refers to a significant negative impact or delay that would substantially affect the ability of a legal entity to perform its obligations."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ff621339cc48c1d0afec4e0b8efe1d64</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 29}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TRANSACTIONS CONTEMPLATED HEREBY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Transactions contemplated hereby refer to the financial agreements or arrangements that are the subject of the current document."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ff621339cc48c1d0afec4e0b8efe1d64</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 20}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INFORMATION PROVIDED IN CONNECTION THEREWITH&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Information provided in connection therewith refers to the details and data related to the transactions contemplated hereby."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ff621339cc48c1d0afec4e0b8efe1d64</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 29}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ARTICLE VI&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"ARTICLE VI is a specific section within the document that contains detailed representations and warranties from the Supporting Lenders."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ff621339cc48c1d0afec4e0b8efe1d64</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 32}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;REPRESENTATIONS AND WARRANTIES OF THE SUPPORTING LENDERS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Representations and Warranties of the Supporting Lenders are the commitments made by the Supporting Lenders to the Company regarding their legal status and business operations."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ff621339cc48c1d0afec4e0b8efe1d64</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 32}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SECTION 6.1&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Section 6.1 is a specific clause within ARTICLE VI that focuses on the qualifications and organizational status of the Supporting Lenders."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ff621339cc48c1d0afec4e0b8efe1d64</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;QUALIFICATIONS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Qualifications refer to the legal and operational requirements that a Supporting Lender must meet to be considered validly existing and in good standing."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ff621339cc48c1d0afec4e0b8efe1d64</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 29}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;OPERATION OF ITS PROPERTIES AND ASSETS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Operation of its properties and assets refers to the management and use of physical and tangible resources owned by a Supporting Lender."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ff621339cc48c1d0afec4e0b8efe1d64</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 29}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CONDUCT OF ITS BUSINESS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Conduct of its business refers to the day-to-day activities and operations of a Supporting Lender in fulfilling its business objectives."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ff621339cc48c1d0afec4e0b8efe1d64</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 29}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SEVERALLY AND NOT JOINTLY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Severally and not jointly means that each Supporting Lender is individually responsible for their representations and warranties, and not collectively with the others."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ff621339cc48c1d0afec4e0b8efe1d64</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 29}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COLLECTIVE INTROSPECTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Collective Introspection is the process of deep thinking and reflection by the team about their role in the cosmic play.")&lt;SEP&gt;"Collective introspection refers to the process of reflecting and evaluating the actions and decisions of a group as a whole."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-87d77cafdce8d4afe48dd9e298dcebfa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ff621339cc48c1d0afec4e0b8efe1d64</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 29}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GRAND COSMIC PLAY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Grand Cosmic Play refers to the larger context of the cosmic events and interactions involving the team and the unknown intelligence.")&lt;SEP&gt;"Grand cosmic play refers to the larger context or narrative of the Supporting Lenders' involvement in a significant and potentially historic event or series of events."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-87d77cafdce8d4afe48dd9e298dcebfa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ff621339cc48c1d0afec4e0b8efe1d64</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 29}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ENCRYPTED DIALOGUE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Encrypted Dialogue is a form of communication that is difficult to decipher, often used in secure or confidential exchanges."&lt;SEP&gt;"Encrypted Dialogue refers to the ongoing communication that is unfolding and showing intricate patterns.")&lt;SEP&gt;"Encrypted dialogue refers to a secure and confidential communication channel used for sensitive information exchange."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-87d77cafdce8d4afe48dd9e298dcebfa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ff621339cc48c1d0afec4e0b8efe1d64&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dca9303a607f377e06cf6c0a4f271e11</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 29}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INTRA-TRANSACTIONAL COMMUNICATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Intra-transactional communication refers to the internal communication and coordination among parties involved in a transaction."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ff621339cc48c1d0afec4e0b8efe1d64</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 29}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LEGAL FRAMEWORK&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Legal framework refers to the set of laws, regulations, and guidelines that govern the behavior and operations of legal entities."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ff621339cc48c1d0afec4e0b8efe1d64</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 29}]</data>
</node>
