</node>
<node id="&quot;PARENT COLONY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Parent Colony is a fully established colony that loses a significant portion of its population during swarming, including the laying queen, and faces reduced honey production and potential weakening."&lt;SEP&gt;"Parent Colony is the original bee colony from which the swarm originates, losing about half of its population during the swarming event."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-41c3aaf395c33844b42f907bc25d40ac&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-54cbc98c2355f1563efcd1e13da95f19</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NEW COLONY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"New Colony is the new bee colony formed by the swarm, separate from the parent colony and establishing itself in a new location."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-54cbc98c2355f1563efcd1e13da95f19</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;EGG-LAYING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Egg-Laying is the process by which the queen bee lays eggs, which is crucial for the growth and maintenance of the colony."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-54cbc98c2355f1563efcd1e13da95f19</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;QUEEN CELLS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Queen Cells are structures within the hive where new queens are reared, ensuring the continuity of the colony."&lt;SEP&gt;"Queen Cells are structures within the hive where new queens develop, playing a critical role in swarm prevention and colony management."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-41c3aaf395c33844b42f907bc25d40ac&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-54cbc98c2355f1563efcd1e13da95f19</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HARASSMENT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Harassment is the behavior of worker bees to shake and maul the queen, helping to prepare her for swarming."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-54cbc98c2355f1563efcd1e13da95f19</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FEEDING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Feeding is the process by which worker bees provide sustenance to the queen, which affects her egg-laying rate."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-54cbc98c2355f1563efcd1e13da95f19</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;STIMULATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Stimulation is the factor that influences the queen's egg-laying rate, controlled by the worker bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-54cbc98c2355f1563efcd1e13da95f19</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FLYING TRIM&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Flying Trim is the condition of the queen bee that allows her to fly effectively, necessary for swarming."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-54cbc98c2355f1563efcd1e13da95f19</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NEW ADULT QUEEN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"New Adult Queen is the new queen bee that emerges after the swarm has left, taking over the egg-laying responsibilities of the parent colony."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-54cbc98c2355f1563efcd1e13da95f19</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PARENT COLONY POPULATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Parent Colony Population refers to the number of bees in the original colony before the swarming event."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-54cbc98c2355f1563efcd1e13da95f19</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NEW COLONY ESTABLISHMENT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"New Colony Establishment is the process by which the swarm forms a new colony in a new location."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-54cbc98c2355f1563efcd1e13da95f19</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NEW QUEEN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"New Queen is a young female bee that develops from a Queen Cell and eventually becomes the new queen of the colony."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-41c3aaf395c33844b42f907bc25d40ac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LAYING QUEEN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Laying Queen is the current queen of the colony responsible for laying eggs and maintaining the colony's population."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-41c3aaf395c33844b42f907bc25d40ac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CONGESTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Congestion refers to a condition within the hive where there are too many bees, leading to stress and potential swarming."&lt;SEP&gt;"Congestion refers to the crowded conditions within the hive that can trigger the swarm impulse."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-41c3aaf395c33844b42f907bc25d40ac&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7744ce257d4323a8eb4027b5dc0cb920</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WINTER PREPARATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Winter Preparation is the process by which the colony prepares for the harsh winter months."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-41c3aaf395c33844b42f907bc25d40ac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ENVIRONMENTAL CONDITIONS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Environmental conditions include factors such as temperature, humidity, and availability of food sources that influence swarming behavior."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-7744ce257d4323a8eb4027b5dc0cb920</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NEW BEEKEEPER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"New beekeeper is a person who is just starting to learn about beekeeping and managing bee colonies."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-7744ce257d4323a8eb4027b5dc0cb920</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NUTRITION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Nutrition is the provision of essential substances required by organisms for growth, maintenance, and repair, crucial for bee health."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-7744ce257d4323a8eb4027b5dc0cb920</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BEEKEEPING ASSOCIATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Beekeeping association is an organization that provides resources and support to beekeepers."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-7744ce257d4323a8eb4027b5dc0cb920</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HONEY PRODUCTION REGION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Honey production region is an area known for its high nectar and pollen production, supporting bee colonies."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-7744ce257d4323a8eb4027b5dc0cb920</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SWARMING SEASON&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Swarming season is a period when swarms are more likely to occur due to favorable environmental conditions."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-7744ce257d4323a8eb4027b5dc0cb920</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BEEKEEPING CONFERENCE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Beekeeping conference is an event where beekeepers gather to learn about swarm control and prevention techniques."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-7744ce257d4323a8eb4027b5dc0cb920</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COMPANY REGISTERED INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Company Registered Intellectual Property refers to intellectual property items owned by the company and its subsidiaries, which are subsisting, valid, and enforceable."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8300f5060c70067c2752417b5bf332bf</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 24}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PERMITTED ENCUMBRANCES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Permitted Encumbrances refer to acceptable limitations or restrictions on the Company Intellectual Property that do not affect its validity or enforceability."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8300f5060c70067c2752417b5bf332bf</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 24}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ORDER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"An Order refers to any legal directive that could affect the validity or enforceability of the company's intellectual property."&lt;SEP&gt;"Order refers to any legal directive that could adversely affect or restrict the validity or enforceability of the Company Intellectual Property."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-05c8b19983470d6fbb9ef38e0630e896&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8300f5060c70067c2752417b5bf332bf</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 2}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 24}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INTERNET DOMAIN NAME REGISTRAR&quot;">
