  <data key="d1">"Glottic Valve Development is the developmental process of the valve-like structure that controls the passage of air through the glottis."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-dca9303a607f377e06cf6c0a4f271e11</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GLOTTIC CLOSURE MECHANISM DEVELOPMENT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Glottic Closure Mechanism Development is the developmental process of the mechanism by which the glottis is closed, either gently to produce sound or firmly to prevent foreign objects from entering the lungs."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-dca9303a607f377e06cf6c0a4f271e11</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GLOTTIC OPENING MECHANISM DEVELOPMENT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Glottic Opening Mechanism Development is the developmental process of the mechanism by which the glottis is opened, allowing air to pass through the larynx."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-dca9303a607f377e06cf6c0a4f271e11</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GLOTTIC VIBRATION MECHANISM DEVELOPMENT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Glottic Vibration Mechanism Development is the developmental process of the mechanism by which the vocal folds vibrate to produce sound."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-dca9303a607f377e06cf6c0a4f271e11</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GLOTTIC TISSUE EVOLUTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Glottic Tissue Evolution is the evolutionary process of the tissue that forms the glottis, which is the space between the vocal folds."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-dca9303a607f377e06cf6c0a4f271e11</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GLOTTIC FLAP EVOLUTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Glottic Flap Evolution is the evolutionary process of the flap of tissue that forms part of the glottis, which is the space between the vocal folds."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-dca9303a607f377e06cf6c0a4f271e11</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GLOTTIC VALVE EVOLUTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Glottic Valve Evolution is the evolutionary process of the valve-like structure that controls the passage of air through the glottis."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-dca9303a607f377e06cf6c0a4f271e11</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GLOTTIC CLOSURE MECHANISM EVOLUTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Glottic Closure Mechanism Evolution is the evolutionary process of the mechanism by which the glottis is closed, either gently to produce sound or firmly to prevent foreign objects from entering the lungs."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-dca9303a607f377e06cf6c0a4f271e11</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GLOTTIC OPENING MECHANISM EVOLUTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Glottic Opening Mechanism Evolution is the evolutionary process of the mechanism by which the glottis is opened, allowing air to pass through the larynx."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-dca9303a607f377e06cf6c0a4f271e11</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GLOTTIC VIBRATION MECHANISM EVOLUTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Glottic Vibration Mechanism Evolution is the evolutionary process of the mechanism by which the vocal folds vibrate to produce sound."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-dca9303a607f377e06cf6c0a4f271e11</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GLOTTIC TISSUE HOMEOSTASIS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Glottic Tissue Homeostasis is the maintenance of a stable internal environment in the tissue that forms the glottis, which is the space between the vocal folds."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-dca9303a607f377e06cf6c0a4f271e11</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GLOTTIC FLAP HOMEOSTASIS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Glottic Flap Homeostasis is the maintenance of a stable internal environment in the flap of tissue that forms part of the glottis, which is the space between the vocal folds."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-dca9303a607f377e06cf6c0a4f271e11</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GLOTTIC VALVE HOMEOSTASIS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Glottic Valve Homeostasis is the maintenance of a stable internal environment in the valve-like structure that controls the passage of air through the glottis."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-dca9303a607f377e06cf6c0a4f271e11</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GLOTTIC CLOSURE MECHANISM HOMEOSTASIS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Glottic Closure Mechanism Homeostasis is the maintenance of a stable internal environment in the mechanism by which the glottis is closed, either gently to produce sound or firmly to prevent foreign objects from entering the lungs."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-dca9303a607f377e06cf6c0a4f271e11</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GLOTTIC OPENING MECHANISM HOMEOSTASIS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Glottic Opening Mechanism Homeostasis is the maintenance of a stable internal environment in the mechanism by which the glottis is opened, allowing air to pass through the larynx."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-dca9303a607f377e06cf6c0a4f271e11</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GLOTTIC VIBRATION MECHANISM HOMEOSTASIS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Glottic Vibration Mechanism Homeostasis is the maintenance of a stable internal environment in the mechanism by which the vocal folds vibrate to produce sound."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-dca9303a607f377e06cf6c0a4f271e11</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GLOTTIC TISSUE METABOLISM&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Glottic Tissue Metabolism is the metabolic processes occurring in the tissue that forms the glottis, which is the space between the vocal folds."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-dca9303a607f377e06cf6c0a4f271e11</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GLOTTIC FLAP METABOLISM&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Glottic Flap Metabolism is the metabolic processes occurring in the flap of tissue that forms part of the glottis, which is the space between the vocal folds."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-dca9303a607f377e06cf6c0a4f271e11</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GLOTTIC VALVE METABOLISM&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Glottic Valve Metabolism is the metabolic processes occurring in the valve-like structure that controls the passage of air through the glottis."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-dca9303a607f377e06cf6c0a4f271e11</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WOMEN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Women have a smaller glottis compared to men, specifically about the size of a dime."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1b275cbb65dda44f47ce44df6a2fb9cd</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 1}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 16}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MEN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Men have a larger glottis compared to women, approaching the diameter of a quarter."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1b275cbb65dda44f47ce44df6a2fb9cd</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 1}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 16}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ABDUCTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Abduction is the action where the vocal folds open in the shape of the letter V during normal breathing."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1b275cbb65dda44f47ce44df6a2fb9cd</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 1}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 15}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ADDUCTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Adduction is the action where the vocal folds close to produce sound during phonation."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1b275cbb65dda44f47ce44df6a2fb9cd</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 1}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 15}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LAMINA PROPRIA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The lamina propria is a layer of gelatinous material surrounding the core muscle of the vocal folds, providing support and flexibility."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1b275cbb65dda44f47ce44df6a2fb9cd</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 1}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 18}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VOCAL LIGAMENT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The vocal ligament runs through the lamina propria and helps prevent injury by limiting the stretch of the vocal folds for high pitches."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1b275cbb65dda44f47ce44df6a2fb9cd</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 1}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 18}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;EPITHELIAL LAYER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The epithelial layer is a thin, hairless layer that surrounds the vocal folds and is kept moist with mucus."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1b275cbb65dda44f47ce44df6a2fb9cd</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 1}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 17}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CORE MUSCLE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The core muscle forms the inner layer of the vocal folds, providing the necessary movement for sound production."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1b275cbb65dda44f47ce44df6a2fb9cd</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 1}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 15}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MUCUS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Mucus is a secretion from the throat, larynx, and trachea that keeps the epithelial layer of the vocal folds moist."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1b275cbb65dda44f47ce44df6a2fb9cd</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 1}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 17}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WAVELIKE MOTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"During phonation, the outer layer of the vocal folds glides independently over the inner layer in a wavelike motion, essential for sound production."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1b275cbb65dda44f47ce44df6a2fb9cd</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 1}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 15}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;THIGH MUSCLES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Thigh muscles are used as an analogy to describe the adduction and abduction movements of the vocal folds, similar to how these muscles work during exercise."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1b275cbb65dda44f47ce44df6a2fb9cd</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 1}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 15}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CHEST MUSCLES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Chest muscles are also used as an analogy to describe the adduction and abduction movements of the vocal folds, similar to how these muscles work during exercise."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-1b275cbb65dda44f47ce44df6a2fb9cd</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 1}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 15}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VOCAL FOLD&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Vocal Fold is a physiological structure involved in phonation, characterized by its layered structure and the independent movement of its inner and outer layers."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-dc4be754ab02233d9e6804456be8d754</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PALM OF THE HAND&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Palm of the Hand is a part of the human hand used as a reference for understanding the attachment of skin to underlying structures."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-dc4be754ab02233d9e6804456be8d754</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BACK OF THE HAND&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Back of the Hand is another part of the human hand used as a reference for understanding the attachment of skin to underlying structures."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-dc4be754ab02233d9e6804456be8d754</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SKIN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Skin is the outer covering of the body, attached to the flesh beneath it, and can be either firmly or loosely attached depending on the area of the body."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-dc4be754ab02233d9e6804456be8d754</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FLESH&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Flesh is the soft tissue beneath the skin, providing padding and support for the underlying bones."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-dc4be754ab02233d9e6804456be8d754</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BONE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Bone is the rigid connective tissue forming the skeleton, protected by the skin and flesh."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-dc4be754ab02233d9e6804456be8d754</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PHONATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Phonation is the act of producing sound using the vocal folds."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-dc4be754ab02233d9e6804456be8d754</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WAVERING MOTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Wavering Motion describes the wavelike motion of the outer layer of the vocal fold over the inner layer, crucial for phonation."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-dc4be754ab02233d9e6804456be8d754</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INDEPENDENT MOVEMENT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Independent Movement refers to the separate actions of the inner and outer layers of the vocal fold, essential for phonation."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-dc4be754ab02233d9e6804456be8d754</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LAYERED STRUCTURE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Layered Structure describes the composition of the vocal fold, consisting of an outer layer and an inner layer."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-dc4be754ab02233d9e6804456be8d754</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FOLD&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Fold is a specific anatomical structure within the vocal fold, contributing to its function."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-dc4be754ab02233d9e6804456be8d754</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INNER LAYER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Inner Layer is the deeper part of the vocal fold that moves independently of the outer layer."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-dc4be754ab02233d9e6804456be8d754</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;OUTER LAYER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Outer Layer is the surface part of the vocal fold that glides independently over the inner layer."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-dc4be754ab02233d9e6804456be8d754</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INFORMATION RELATING TO SUPPORTING LENDERS OR COMPANY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Information Relating to Supporting Lenders or Company includes details about financial support and the company's operations."</data>
