  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"These are various forms of regulatory approvals or permissions required for the transactions."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-50c13e3bb8e4150848f52b75b8673473</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 4}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 30}, {"level": 2, "cluster": 53}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;EFFECTIVE PERIOD&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Effective Period is the duration during which certain provisions of the agreement are in effect."&lt;SEP&gt;"Effective Period is the duration during which certain provisions of the agreement are in effect.")</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0098193a3d104a7324b88d9086bac046</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;EMPLOYEE COMMUNICATIONS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Employee Communications refers to the process of making broad-based written or oral communications to officers and employees of the Company or its Subsidiaries regarding compensation or benefit matters."&lt;SEP&gt;"Employee Communications refers to the process of making broad-based written or oral communications to officers and employees of the Company or its Subsidiaries regarding compensation or benefit matters.")</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0098193a3d104a7324b88d9086bac046</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RICICULTURE AND COOPERATIVE EXTENSION SYSTEM&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Riciculture and Cooperative Extension System refers to agricultural practices and support systems, though not directly related to the main agreement, it is mentioned separately."&lt;SEP&gt;"Riciculture and Cooperative Extension System refers to agricultural practices and support systems, though not directly related to the main agreement, it is mentioned separately.")</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0098193a3d104a7324b88d9086bac046</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COMPENSATION OR BENEFIT MATTERS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Compensation or Benefit Matters are issues related to employee pay and benefits that are affected by the Transactions."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0098193a3d104a7324b88d9086bac046</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HONEYBEES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Honeybees are insects used in beekeeping for producing honey and pollination."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0098193a3d104a7324b88d9086bac046</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HISTORY OF BEEKEEPING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"History of Beekeeping is the historical context and evolution of beekeeping practices and techniques."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-0098193a3d104a7324b88d9086bac046</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ANCIENT TIMES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Ancient Times represents the period from the beginning of recorded history until around 1500 AD, during which beekeeping practices were established."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d84a5beb18cbfd1e9fa66937ebb5293b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;1500&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"1500 marks the end of the first era of beekeeping and the beginning of the second era, characterized by advancements in hive design and management techniques."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d84a5beb18cbfd1e9fa66937ebb5293b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;1850&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"1850 marks the end of the second era and the beginning of the third era, characterized by significant scientific research and the development of modern beekeeping practices."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d84a5beb18cbfd1e9fa66937ebb5293b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PRESENT DAY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Present Day represents the current time, during which beekeeping is influenced by modern research, increased demand for pollination services, and environmental challenges such as mite infestations and Africanized bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d84a5beb18cbfd1e9fa66937ebb5293b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NATURALLY HOLLOW LOG&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Naturally Hollow Log refers to the earliest known type of beehive, which was used by primitive people and remained in use until the 20th century."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d84a5beb18cbfd1e9fa66937ebb5293b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HONEY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PRODUCT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Honey is a product harvested from bees, often associated with beekeeping practices and valued for its nutritional and medicinal properties."&lt;SEP&gt;"Honey is the primary product collected from bees, often obtained from natural nests or hollow trees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d84a5beb18cbfd1e9fa66937ebb5293b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e12a53f3b6ece3d5992379cab9e9f17b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COMMERCIAL POLLINATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ACTIVITY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Commercial Pollination involves the use of managed bee colonies to pollinate crops, ensuring higher yields and better quality produce."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d84a5beb18cbfd1e9fa66937ebb5293b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ENVIRONMENTAL CHALLENGES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Environmental Challenges refer to various issues affecting bee populations, such as mite infestations and climate change, which impact beekeeping practices."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d84a5beb18cbfd1e9fa66937ebb5293b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;AFRICANIZED HONEY BEE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"SPECIES"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Africanized Honey Bee is a subspecies of the Western honey bee known for its aggressive behavior and rapid spread, posing challenges to beekeepers."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d84a5beb18cbfd1e9fa66937ebb5293b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MITE INFESTATIONS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONDITION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Mite infestations are a common problem in beekeeping, causing significant harm to bee colonies and requiring specialized treatments."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d84a5beb18cbfd1e9fa66937ebb5293b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SKEP&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A skep is a domed hive made of twisted straw, used in more advanced societies as an immediate precursor to modern wooden hives."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e12a53f3b6ece3d5992379cab9e9f17b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;EARLY HIVES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Early hives were crude structures made from various materials such as pottery, woven material, mud and wattle, or sections of hollow logs, designed for housing bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e12a53f3b6ece3d5992379cab9e9f17b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COLONIES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Colonies refer to groups of bees living together, managed in hives, and whose survival was crucial for honey production."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e12a53f3b6ece3d5992379cab9e9f17b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COMBS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Combs are structures built by bees within their hives, containing honey and brood cells, which were difficult to remove without damaging the colony."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e12a53f3b6ece3d5992379cab9e9f17b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CRUDE HIVES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Crude hives were simple structures used in early times, accessed from the bottom or end, and lacked methods for removing honey without harming the colony."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e12a53f3b6ece3d5992379cab9e9f17b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TOOLS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Tools refer to the limited equipment available to early beekeepers, which constrained the size and design of hives."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e12a53f3b6ece3d5992379cab9e9f17b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WINTER LOSSES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Winter losses refer to the decline in bee populations during cold months, which could be mitigated by encouraging swarming."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e12a53f3b6ece3d5992379cab9e9f17b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;HOLLOW LOGS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"MATERIAL"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Hollow logs were used as early hives, providing a natural nesting site for bees."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e12a53f3b6ece3d5992379cab9e9f17b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ADVANCED SOCIETIES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Advanced societies employed more sophisticated methods, including the use of skeps, to manage bees and improve honey production."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e12a53f3b6ece3d5992379cab9e9f17b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MODERN WOODEN HIVES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Modern wooden hives are the current standard in beekeeping, replacing earlier crude designs and offering better management capabilities."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e12a53f3b6ece3d5992379cab9e9f17b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BOTTOM ACCESS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"FEATURE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Bottom access was a common feature in early hives, allowing for basic management but limiting the ease of honey collection."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e12a53f3b6ece3d5992379cab9e9f17b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;END ACCESS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"FEATURE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"End access was another common feature in early hives, providing alternative entry points for managing the hives."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e12a53f3b6ece3d5992379cab9e9f17b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CUTTING COMBS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"METHOD"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Cutting combs was the only known method for removing honey from early hives, but it resulted in the death of the colony."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e12a53f3b6ece3d5992379cab9e9f17b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CRUSHING COMBS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"METHOD"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Crushing combs was another method for removing honey, which also led to the death of the colony due to the destruction of the comb."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e12a53f3b6ece3d5992379cab9e9f17b</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;EARLY BEEKEEPERS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Early Beekeepers refers to the practices and philosophies of beekeeping during the early era, characterized by simple methods and limited understanding of bee biology."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-7251f3651e5cd421ae992f26de8129b2</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ROMAN BEEKEEPERS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Roman Beekeepers refers to the specific group of beekeepers who developed some knowledge about bees, including feeding them and observing their behavior."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-7251f3651e5cd421ae992f26de8129b2</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;REMOVABLE COMB&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Removable Comb is a tool or method that allows beekeepers to observe and manipulate the internal structure of the hive without damaging it, crucial for understanding bee biology."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-7251f3651e5cd421ae992f26de8129b2</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WAX&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Wax is a substance produced by bees, used for constructing the comb and storing honey, recognized by early beekeepers but misunderstood in terms of its origin."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-7251f3651e5cd421ae992f26de8129b2</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COMB&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Comb is a structure built by bees using wax, used for storing honey and raising larvae."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-7251f3651e5cd421ae992f26de8129b2</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SPERM&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Sperm is the male reproductive cell used by drones to fertilize the queen's eggs."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-7251f3651e5cd421ae992f26de8129b2</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MONARCH&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Monarch refers to the queen bee, the dominant female in the hive."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-7251f3651e5cd421ae992f26de8129b2</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;EGGS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Eggs are laid in the cells of the hive.")&lt;SEP&gt;"Eggs are the reproductive cells laid by the queen bee, which can develop into workers, drones, or new queens."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-7251f3651e5cd421ae992f26de8129b2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-573b4d1e9d950dca730f99b82578a0ac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FOOD&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Food refers to the resources needed by the colony, particularly honey and nectar, which are stored in the comb."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-7251f3651e5cd421ae992f26de8129b2</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VIBRATOR&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Vibrator is transformed into sounds we identify as a piano, trumpet, or guitar.")</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-573b4d1e9d950dca730f99b82578a0ac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INSTRUMENTS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Instruments require a means of articulation to create the nuanced sounds of music.")</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-573b4d1e9d950dca730f99b82578a0ac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PULMONARY SYSTEM&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Pulmonary System provides power for the human voice and singing.")</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-573b4d1e9d950dca730f99b82578a0ac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RESPIRATORY SYSTEM&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Respiratory System is crucial for sustaining long phrases in singing and exchanging blood gases.")</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-573b4d1e9d950dca730f99b82578a0ac</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 13}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;EXCHANGE OF BLOOD GASES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Breathing is essential for the exchange of blood gases—oxygen in, carbon dioxide out.")</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-573b4d1e9d950dca730f99b82578a0ac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FRESH OXYGEN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Fresh oxygen is needed before the lungs are totally empty during sustained phrases.")</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-573b4d1e9d950dca730f99b82578a0ac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MISCONCEPTIONS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Misconceptions about breathing for singing are common and need to be dispelled.")</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-573b4d1e9d950dca730f99b82578a0ac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SOUND SOURCE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Both the human voice and a trumpet use flaps of tissue as a sound source.")</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-573b4d1e9d950dca730f99b82578a0ac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RESONATOR&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Both the human voice and a trumpet use hollow tubes as resonators.")</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-573b4d1e9d950dca730f99b82578a0ac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;STORAGE DEPOT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The respiratory system acts as a storage depot for the air used to produce sound.")</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-573b4d1e9d950dca730f99b82578a0ac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CONFLICT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"There can be a conflict between sustaining a long phrase and needing fresh oxygen.")</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-573b4d1e9d950dca730f99b82578a0ac</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BOYLE'S LAW&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Boyle's Law is a principle in physics stating that the pressure of a gas within a container changes inversely with changes in volume, explaining aspects of breathing and lung mechanics."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-758eb501fb5470d3f4e2fe61badac423</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NATURE ABHORS A VACUUM&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Nature Abhors a Vacuum is a principle stating that air will flow from areas of higher pressure to areas of lower pressure to equalize the pressure, explaining how air moves during breathing."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-758eb501fb5470d3f4e2fe61badac423</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ALVEOLI&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Alveoli are tiny air sacs in the lungs where gas exchange occurs, functioning like miniature bladders to store air for use in vocal fold vibration."&lt;SEP&gt;"Alveoli are tiny air sacs in the lungs where gases are exchanged and act like miniature bladders for storing air to set vocal folds into vibration."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-758eb501fb5470d3f4e2fe61badac423&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3fb90ae6bf97fbc21cb066ced098ee6c</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 1}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 15}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DIAPHRAGM&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"MUSCLE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The diaphragm is a dome-shaped muscle located at the base of the lungs, originating from the bottom of the sternum and extending around the ribs to the spine, serving as the primary muscle of inspiration."&lt;SEP&gt;"The diaphragm is the second largest muscle in the body, located between the chest and abdomen, responsible for breathing by contracting and moving downward during inhalation."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-116b7be2fde255bf1bbeef908b472818&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3fb90ae6bf97fbc21cb066ced098ee6c</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 44}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INSPIRATORY FUNCTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"FUNCTION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Inspiratory Function refers to the action of muscles that increase the volume capacity of the thorax to facilitate inhalation."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-3fb90ae6bf97fbc21cb066ced098ee6c</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 44}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;EXPIRATORY FUNCTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"FUNCTION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Expiratory Function refers to the action of muscles that decrease the volume capacity of the thorax to facilitate exhalation."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-3fb90ae6bf97fbc21cb066ced098ee6c</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 12}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;STERNUM&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ANATOMY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The Sternum, or breastbone, is the flat bone in the center of the chest from which the diaphragm originates."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-3fb90ae6bf97fbc21cb066ced098ee6c</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 9}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 44}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RIB CAGE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ANATOMY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The Rib Cage is part of the thorax, which is enlarged and compressed by special muscles to aid in breathing."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-3fb90ae6bf97fbc21cb066ced098ee6c</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 12}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SPINE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ANATOMY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The Spine is part of the thorax, which is enlarged and compressed by special muscles to aid in breathing."&lt;SEP&gt;"The spine is a column of vertebrae that supports the upper body and protects the spinal cord."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-116b7be2fde255bf1bbeef908b472818&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3fb90ae6bf97fbc21cb066ced098ee6c</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 12}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SPECIAL MUSCLES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"MUSCLE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Special Muscles are designed to enlarge and compress the thorax to aid in breathing, including the diaphragm and intercostal muscles."&lt;SEP&gt;"Special muscles are designed to enlarge and compress the thorax to aid in breathing, including the diaphragm and intercostal muscles."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-3fb90ae6bf97fbc21cb066ced098ee6c</data>
  <data key="d3">[{"level": 0, "cluster": 0}, {"level": 1, "cluster": 12}]</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GAS EXCHANGE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PROCESS"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Gas Exchange is the process of exchanging oxygen and carbon dioxide between the alveoli and the blood, facilitated by the lungs."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-3fb90ae6bf97fbc21cb066ced098ee6c</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GASES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"SUBSTANCE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Gases are exchanged in the lungs, specifically in the alveoli, for respiration."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-3fb90ae6bf97fbc21cb066ced098ee6c</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BLADDER FOR A BAG PIPE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"METAPHOR"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The alveoli are compared to a bladder for a bag pipe, storing air for vocal fold vibration."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-3fb90ae6bf97fbc21cb066ced098ee6c</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VOCAL FOLD VIBRATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PROCESS"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Vocal folds vibrate due to air from the lungs, specifically from the alveoli."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-3fb90ae6bf97fbc21cb066ced098ee6c</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INTERCOSTAL MUSCLES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"MUSCLE"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Intercostal muscles are a type of special muscle that help in the expansion and contraction of the thorax."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-3fb90ae6bf97fbc21cb066ced098ee6c</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;THORACIC CAVITY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ANATOMY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The Thoracic Cavity is another term for the thorax, which includes the rib cage and other components."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-3fb90ae6bf97fbc21cb066ced098ee6c</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INHALATION PROCESS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PROCESS"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Inhalation is the process of taking air into the lungs, facilitated by the enlargement of the thorax."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-3fb90ae6bf97fbc21cb066ced098ee6c</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;EXHALATION PROCESS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PROCESS"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Exhalation is the process of expelling air from the lungs, facilitated by the compression of the thorax."</data>
