  <data key="d4">20.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The amygdala signals the hypothalamus to initiate a fight-or-flight response."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-9fa546cd3293c9b8d7663bb92b9e876e</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HYPOTHALAMUS&quot;" target="&quot;ADRENAL GLANDS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">38.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Hypothalamus signals the adrenal glands to release adrenaline."&lt;SEP&gt;"The hypothalamus signals the adrenal glands to release adrenaline."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-9fa546cd3293c9b8d7663bb92b9e876e</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HYPOTHALAMUS&quot;" target="&quot;NEURONS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Neurons in the brain transmit signals to the hypothalamus."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-9fa546cd3293c9b8d7663bb92b9e876e</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HYPOTHALAMUS&quot;" target="&quot;HEART&quot;">
  <data key="d4">20.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Hypothalamus signals the heart to increase its beating rate."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-9fa546cd3293c9b8d7663bb92b9e876e</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HYPOTHALAMUS&quot;" target="&quot;LUNGS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">20.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Hypothalamus signals the lungs to increase their breathing rate."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-9fa546cd3293c9b8d7663bb92b9e876e</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HYPOTHALAMUS&quot;" target="&quot;SKELETAL MUSCLES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">20.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Hypothalamus signals the skeletal muscles to increase their contraction."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-9fa546cd3293c9b8d7663bb92b9e876e</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HYPOTHALAMUS&quot;" target="&quot;LIVER&quot;">
  <data key="d4">20.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Hypothalamus signals the liver to release stored sugar for energy."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-9fa546cd3293c9b8d7663bb92b9e876e</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HYPOTHALAMUS&quot;" target="&quot;SMOOTH MUSCLES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">20.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Hypothalamus signals the smooth muscles to respond to adrenaline."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-9fa546cd3293c9b8d7663bb92b9e876e</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HYPOTHALAMUS&quot;" target="&quot;PITUITARY GLAND&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The hypothalamus sends corticotropin-releasing factor (CRF) to the pituitary gland, triggering the release of adrenocorticotropic hormone (ACTH)."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-93bc63283f93b5a59465f5c505cc5ad3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HYPOTHALAMUS&quot;" target="&quot;ADRENAL GLAND&quot;">
  <data key="d4">128.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The hypothalamus indirectly affects the adrenal gland through the release of corticotropin-releasing factor (CRF), which triggers the release of cortisol and adrenaline during stress responses."&lt;SEP&gt;"Through the pituitary gland, the hypothalamus indirectly triggers the adrenal gland to release cortisol and adrenaline in response to stress."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-93bc63283f93b5a59465f5c505cc5ad3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HYPOTHALAMUS&quot;" target="&quot;SMOOTH MUSCLE CELLS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">119.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The hypothalamus indirectly affects smooth muscle cells through the release of corticotropin-releasing factor (CRF), which leads to physiological responses such as constriction of blood vessels and standing of skin hairs during stress responses."&lt;SEP&gt;"The hypothalamus indirectly affects smooth muscle cells through the release of corticotropin-releasing factor (CRF), which leads to physiological responses such as constriction of blood vessels and standing of skin hairs."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-93bc63283f93b5a59465f5c505cc5ad3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HYPOTHALAMUS&quot;" target="&quot;MY HEART&quot;">
  <data key="d4">119.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The hypothalamus indirectly affects my heart through the release of corticotropin-releasing factor (CRF), which leads to increased heart rate and blood flow during stress responses."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-93bc63283f93b5a59465f5c505cc5ad3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HYPOTHALAMUS&quot;" target="&quot;MY LUNGS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">119.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The hypothalamus indirectly affects my lungs through the release of corticotropin-releasing factor (CRF), which leads to increased breathing rate during stress responses."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-93bc63283f93b5a59465f5c505cc5ad3</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;HYPOTHALAMUS&quot;" target="&quot;MY SKELETAL MUSCLES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">119.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The hypothalamus indirectly affects my skeletal muscles through the release of corticotropin-releasing factor (CRF), which leads to increased muscle contraction during stress responses."&lt;SEP&gt;"The hypothalamus indirectly affects my skeletal muscles through therelease of corticotropin-releasing factor (CRF), which leads to increased muscle contraction during stress responses."</data>
