  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bees are attracted to the color and scent of socks, making them a primary target for bees."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a3359e9ea7553a8920a2aaf90b589a9d</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;RED&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bees perceive the color red as black, reducing the likelihood of attracting them."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a3359e9ea7553a8920a2aaf90b589a9d</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;PERFUME&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Perfume is attractive to bees, causing them to investigate and potentially become tangled in clothing or hair."</data>
