<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;ALARM ODOR&quot;">
  <data key="d4">5.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Alarm odor is the scent released by bees when they sting, which can be mistaken for the smell of bananas, though this was tested and found to be false."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a3359e9ea7553a8920a2aaf90b589a9d</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;HONEY PRODUCTION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bees are responsible for honey production, which is an important activity for their survival and for humans."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a3359e9ea7553a8920a2aaf90b589a9d</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;POLLINATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bees are responsible for pollination, which is crucial for plant reproduction and ecosystem health."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a3359e9ea7553a8920a2aaf90b589a9d</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;ENTRANCE BOARD&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bees use the entrance board to enter and exit the hive, often observed by beekeepers."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a3359e9ea7553a8920a2aaf90b589a9d</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;DRONE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">6.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Drone is a type of bee, male and non-reproductive, often found in hives and involved in mating with queens."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-a3359e9ea7553a8920a2aaf90b589a9d</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;HOLLOW LOGS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bees naturally chose hollow logs as nesting sites, which were utilized in early beekeeping practices."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-e12a53f3b6ece3d5992379cab9e9f17b</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BEES&quot;" target="&quot;POLLEN PELLETS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bees carry pollen pellets that could be mistaken for wax."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-573b4d1e9d950dca730f99b82578a0ac</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
