  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bees carry pollen pellets that could be mistaken for wax."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-573b4d1e9d950dca730f99b82578a0ac</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SWARMS&quot;" target="&quot;HOLLOW TREE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Swarms prefer Hollow Trees as a new home due to their natural suitability."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-fe239287d5735b89f51e1b54e606f90b</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VISIBILITY AND ACCESSIBILITY&quot;" target="&quot;SUNLIGHT&quot;">
  <data key="d4">6.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Visibility and Accessibility is influenced by Sunlight, which affects the bees' preference for a location."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-fe239287d5735b89f51e1b54e606f90b</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VISIBILITY AND ACCESSIBILITY&quot;" target="&quot;ENTRANCE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">5.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Visibility and Accessibility includes the presence of a visible and appropriately lit Entrance for the bees."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-fe239287d5735b89f51e1b54e606f90b</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VISIBILITY AND ACCESSIBILITY&quot;" target="&quot;NEIGHBORS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">4.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Neighbors' apprehensions are influenced by the Visibility and Accessibility of the hive location."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-fe239287d5735b89f51e1b54e606f90b</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VISIBILITY AND ACCESSIBILITY&quot;" target="&quot;STUDY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">10.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"A study on visibility and accessibility could provide insights into managing hives effectively."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-266ae9d398bf7940b640589e500926ee</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;NEIGHBORS&quot;" target="&quot;HIVES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Neighbors' apprehensions can affect the visibility and management of hives, impacting the beekeeper’s actions."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-266ae9d398bf7940b640589e500926ee</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SWARM&quot;" target="&quot;COLONY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Colony is preparing for the Swarm event."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-e52c63f43f0f8ca942825a1048d86e1e</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SWARM&quot;" target="&quot;QUEEN BEE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Swarm is triggered by the Queen Bee's actions of reducing her egg laying rate."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-e52c63f43f0f8ca942825a1048d86e1e</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SWARM&quot;" target="&quot;WORKER BEES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Worker Bees prepare for the swarm by rearing new queens and harassing the current queen to get her in flying condition."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-54cbc98c2355f1563efcd1e13da95f19</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SWARM&quot;" target="&quot;PARENT COLONY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">38.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Swarm occurs when the Parent Colony loses about half of its population, leaving behind a reduced workforce."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Parent Colony loses half its population and a laying Queen during a Swarm event, significantly impacting its health and productivity."&lt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-41c3aaf395c33844b42f907bc25d40ac&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-54cbc98c2355f1563efcd1e13da95f19</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SWARM&quot;" target="&quot;NEW COLONY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Swarm results in the formation of a New Colony, which establishes itself in a new location and becomes a separate entity from the Parent Colony."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-54cbc98c2355f1563efcd1e13da95f19</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SWARM&quot;" target="&quot;PARENT COLONY POPULATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">20.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Swarm results in the loss of about half of the Parent Colony Population."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-54cbc98c2355f1563efcd1e13da95f19</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SWARM&quot;" target="&quot;NEW COLONY ESTABLISHMENT&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Swarm leads to the establishment of a new colony in a new location."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-54cbc98c2355f1563efcd1e13da95f19</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SWARM&quot;" target="&quot;BEEKEEPER&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Beekeepers must understand and manage the Swarm event to maintain colony health and productivity."&lt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-41c3aaf395c33844b42f907bc25d40ac</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SWARM&quot;" target="&quot;QUEEN&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The absence of a laying Queen for up to 4 weeks during a Swarm event adversely affects the colony's population and honey production."&lt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-41c3aaf395c33844b42f907bc25d40ac</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SWARM&quot;" target="&quot;QUEEN CELLS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">12.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Queen Cells are essential for swarm prevention as they allow the colony to prepare for the emergence of a new Queen."&lt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-41c3aaf395c33844b42f907bc25d40ac</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SWARM&quot;" target="&quot;SUPERS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">10.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Adding Supers can help prevent swarming by providing more space, but must be done carefully to avoid triggering the swarm impulse."&lt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-41c3aaf395c33844b42f907bc25d40ac</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SWARM&quot;" target="&quot;SWARM IMPULSE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Swarm Impulse is a compelling force that drives the colony to swarm, and understanding it is crucial for effective swarm control."&lt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-41c3aaf395c33844b42f907bc25d40ac</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SWARM&quot;" target="&quot;SWARM CONTROL&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Swarm Control involves managing the Swarm event to prevent significant loss of population and productivity."&lt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-41c3aaf395c33844b42f907bc25d40ac</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SWARM&quot;" target="&quot;HIVE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Hive is the structure where the Swarm event occurs."&lt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-41c3aaf395c33844b42f907bc25d40ac</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SWARM&quot;" target="&quot;LAYING QUEEN&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The absence of a laying Queen for up to 4 weeks during a Swarm event adversely affects the colony's population and honey production."&lt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-41c3aaf395c33844b42f907bc25d40ac</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SWARM&quot;" target="&quot;NEW QUEEN&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The New Queen plays a role in the Winter Preparation process."&lt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-41c3aaf395c33844b42f907bc25d40ac</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SWARM&quot;" target="&quot;CONGESTION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Congestion within the Hive can lead to the Swarm event."&lt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-41c3aaf395c33844b42f907bc25d40ac</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SWARM&quot;" target="&quot;WINTER PREPARATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Winter Preparation can be disrupted by the Swarm event."&lt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-41c3aaf395c33844b42f907bc25d40ac</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SWARM&quot;" target="&quot;EARLY BEEKEEPERS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Early Beekeepers encouraged swarming in the fall to collect honey, but did not fully understand the process."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-7251f3651e5cd421ae992f26de8129b2</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
