<edge source="&quot;THORAX&quot;" target="&quot;DIAPHRAGM&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Diaphragm, a muscle of inspiration, enlarges the Thorax to allow for inhalation."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-3fb90ae6bf97fbc21cb066ced098ee6c</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;THORAX&quot;" target="&quot;EXPIRATORY FUNCTION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Expiratory Function involves muscles that decrease the volume capacity of the thorax, aiding in exhalation."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-3fb90ae6bf97fbc21cb066ced098ee6c</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;THORAX&quot;" target="&quot;RIB CAGE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Rib Cage is a component of the Thorax, which expands and contracts to facilitate breathing."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-3fb90ae6bf97fbc21cb066ced098ee6c</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;THORAX&quot;" target="&quot;SPINE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Spine is a component of the Thorax, which expands and contracts to facilitate breathing."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-3fb90ae6bf97fbc21cb066ced098ee6c</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;THORAX&quot;" target="&quot;SPECIAL MUSCLES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Special Muscles, such as the diaphragm, enlarge and compress the Thorax to facilitate breathing."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-3fb90ae6bf97fbc21cb066ced098ee6c</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;EXHALATION&quot;" target="&quot;DIAPHRAGM&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Exhalation is facilitated by the relaxation of the Diaphragm, which compresses the thorax."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-3fb90ae6bf97fbc21cb066ced098ee6c</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;INHALATION&quot;" target="&quot;DIAPHRAGM&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Inhalation is facilitated by the contraction of the Diaphragm, which enlarges the thorax."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-3fb90ae6bf97fbc21cb066ced098ee6c</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;LAMINA PROPRIA&quot;" target="&quot;VOCAL LIGAMENT&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The vocal ligament runs through the lamina propria and helps prevent injury."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-1b275cbb65dda44f47ce44df6a2fb9cd</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;EPITHELIAL LAYER&quot;" target="&quot;MUCUS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Mucus keeps the epithelial layer of the vocal folds moist."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-1b275cbb65dda44f47ce44df6a2fb9cd</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VOCAL FOLD&quot;" target="&quot;PHONATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Vocal Fold is essential for the act of phonation, which is the production of sound."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-dc4be754ab02233d9e6804456be8d754</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PALM OF THE HAND&quot;" target="&quot;BACK OF THE HAND&quot;">
  <data key="d4">6.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Both areas of the hand are used as references to understand the attachment of skin to underlying structures, though the back of the hand provides more direct insight due to its loose skin."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-dc4be754ab02233d9e6804456be8d754</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SKIN&quot;" target="&quot;FLESH&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Skin is attached to the flesh, providing protection and support for the underlying bones."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-dc4be754ab02233d9e6804456be8d754</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;FLESH&quot;" target="&quot;BONE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Flesh provides padding and support for the bones, protecting them from external impacts."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-dc4be754ab02233d9e6804456be8d754</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PHONATION&quot;" target="&quot;WAVERING MOTION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Wavering Motion is a component of Phonation, contributing to the production of sound."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-dc4be754ab02233d9e6804456be8d754</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PHONATION&quot;" target="&quot;INDEPENDENT MOVEMENT&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Independent Movement is essential for Phonation, allowing the vocal fold to produce sound effectively."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-dc4be754ab02233d9e6804456be8d754</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;LAYERED STRUCTURE&quot;" target="&quot;FOLD&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Layered Structure describes the composition of the Fold, including the Inner and Outer Layers."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-dc4be754ab02233d9e6804456be8d754</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;FOLD&quot;" target="&quot;INNER LAYER&quot;">
  <data key="d4">6.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Inner Layer is part of the Fold, contributing to its function in phonation."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-dc4be754ab02233d9e6804456be8d754</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;FOLD&quot;" target="&quot;OUTER LAYER&quot;">
  <data key="d4">6.0</data>
