  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;FILING&quot;" target="&quot;REVIEW&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Filing requires Review by third parties or Governmental Entities, ensuring compliance with laws and regulations."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-dc4be754ab02233d9e6804456be8d754</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;FILING&quot;" target="&quot;WRITTEN MATERIALS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Written Materials are part of the Filing process, submitted to third parties or Governmental Entities."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-dc4be754ab02233d9e6804456be8d754</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;FILING&quot;" target="&quot;PARTIES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Parties must file documents with government entities."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-4399a6044c475cc6817f92d0cda2f1af</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;THIRD PARTY&quot;" target="&quot;REVIEW&quot;">
  <data key="d4">6.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Third Party is involved in the Review process, receiving and reviewing information from the Company or Supporting Lenders."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-dc4be754ab02233d9e6804456be8d754</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CONSULTATION&quot;" target="&quot;REVIEW&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Consultation is part of the Review process, involving discussions and considerations of views from both parties."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-dc4be754ab02233d9e6804456be8d754</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CONSULTATION&quot;" target="&quot;VIEWS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Views are discussed during Consultation, contributing to the final decision-making process."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-dc4be754ab02233d9e6804456be8d754</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PARTIES&quot;" target="&quot;WAITING PERIOD EXPIRATIONS OR TERMINATIONS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Parties must keep each other informed about the status of waiting period expirations or terminations."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-4399a6044c475cc6817f92d0cda2f1af</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PARTIES&quot;" target="&quot;CONSENTS, CLEARANCES, WAIVERS, LICENSES, ORDERS, REGISTRATIONS, APPROVALS, PERMITS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Parties must keep each other informed about the status of these regulatory matters."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-4399a6044c475cc6817f92d0cda2f1af</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PARTIES&quot;" target="&quot;SUBMISSIONS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Parties must submit documents to government entities."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-4399a6044c475cc6817f92d0cda2f1af</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PARTIES&quot;" target="&quot;BACKGROUND CHECKS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Parties must undergo background checks as part of the filings and submissions."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-4399a6044c475cc6817f92d0cda2f1af</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PARTIES&quot;" target="&quot;REQUESTS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Parties must respond to requests from government entities."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-4399a6044c475cc6817f92d0cda2f1af</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PARTIES&quot;" target="&quot;ANTITRUST LAW&quot;">
  <data key="d4">20.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Parties must comply with Antitrust Law requirements during the Transactions."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-50c13e3bb8e4150848f52b75b8673473</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SKEP&quot;" target="&quot;EARLY HIVES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Skeps are a type of early hive, representing an advancement in hive design from earlier crude structures."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-e12a53f3b6ece3d5992379cab9e9f17b</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;COLONIES&quot;" target="&quot;COMBS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Colonies use combs to store honey and raise brood, which were essential for the survival and productivity of the colony."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-e12a53f3b6ece3d5992379cab9e9f17b</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;COLONIES&quot;" target="&quot;CRUDE HIVES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Crude hives were used to house colonies, but their limitations led to difficulties in managing the colonies and extracting honey without harming them."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-e12a53f3b6ece3d5992379cab9e9f17b</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;TOOLS&quot;" target="&quot;WINTER LOSSES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Limited tools made it difficult to protect colonies from winter losses, encouraging practices like swarming to maintain population levels."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-e12a53f3b6ece3d5992379cab9e9f17b</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;ADVANCED SOCIETIES&quot;" target="&quot;MODERN WOODEN HIVES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Advanced societies developed more advanced hives, leading to the eventual adoption of modern wooden hives."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-e12a53f3b6ece3d5992379cab9e9f17b</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BOTTOM ACCESS&quot;" target="&quot;END ACCESS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">6.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Both bottom and end access were features of early hives, offering different methods for managing the hives but lacking efficient honey removal techniques."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-e12a53f3b6ece3d5992379cab9e9f17b</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CUTTING COMBS&quot;" target="&quot;CRUSHING COMBS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">6.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Both cutting and crushing combs were methods used to remove honey, but both resulted in the death of the colony, highlighting the challenges of early beekeeping."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-e12a53f3b6ece3d5992379cab9e9f17b</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;EARLY BEEKEEPERS&quot;" target="&quot;ROMAN BEEKEEPERS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Roman Beekeepers were part of the broader group of Early Beekeepers, contributing to the development of beekeeping knowledge."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-7251f3651e5cd421ae992f26de8129b2</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;EARLY BEEKEEPERS&quot;" target="&quot;REMOVABLE COMB&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Removable Comb allowed Early Beekeepers to better understand the inner workings of the hive, improving their practices."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-7251f3651e5cd421ae992f26de8129b2</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;EARLY BEEKEEPERS&quot;" target="&quot;WAX&quot;">
  <data key="d4">12.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Early Beekeepers recognized the existence of wax but misunderstood its origin, indicating a gap in their knowledge."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-7251f3651e5cd421ae992f26de8129b2</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;EARLY BEEKEEPERS&quot;" target="&quot;COMB&quot;">
  <data key="d4">12.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Early Beekeepers used the comb to store honey and raise larvae, but lacked the technology to remove it without damaging the hive."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-7251f3651e5cd421ae992f26de8129b2</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;EARLY BEEKEEPERS&quot;" target="&quot;SPERM&quot;">
  <data key="d4">10.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Early Beekeepers did not fully understand the role of sperm in the mating process of bees."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-7251f3651e5cd421ae992f26de8129b2</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;EARLY BEEKEEPERS&quot;" target="&quot;MONARCH&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Early Beekeepers recognized the queen bee as the monarch of the hive but did not fully understand her role."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-7251f3651e5cd421ae992f26de8129b2</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;EARLY BEEKEEPERS&quot;" target="&quot;EGGS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">12.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Early Beekeepers observed the eggs laid by the queen but did not fully understand the development process."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-7251f3651e5cd421ae992f26de8129b2</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;EARLY BEEKEEPERS&quot;" target="&quot;FOOD&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Early Beekeepers understood the importance of food for the colony but lacked the technology to efficiently manage it."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-7251f3651e5cd421ae992f26de8129b2</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VIBRATOR&quot;" target="&quot;SOUNDS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Vibrator is transformed into sounds we identify as a piano, trumpet, or guitar."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-573b4d1e9d950dca730f99b82578a0ac</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;VIBRATOR&quot;" target="&quot;TRANSFORM SOUNDS&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Vibrator is transformed into sounds we identify as a piano, trumpet, or guitar."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-573b4d1e9d950dca730f99b82578a0ac</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;INSTRUMENTS&quot;" target="&quot;ARTICULATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Instruments require a means of articulation to create the nuanced sounds of music."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-573b4d1e9d950dca730f99b82578a0ac</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;INSTRUMENTS&quot;" target="&quot;REQUIRE ARTICULATION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Instruments require a means of articulation to create the nuanced sounds of music."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-573b4d1e9d950dca730f99b82578a0ac</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PULMONARY SYSTEM&quot;" target="&quot;POWER SOURCE&quot;">
  <data key="d4">10.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Pulmonary System provides power for the human voice and singing."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-573b4d1e9d950dca730f99b82578a0ac</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;PULMONARY SYSTEM&quot;" target="&quot;PROVIDE POWER&quot;">
  <data key="d4">20.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Pulmonary System provides power for the human voice and singing."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-573b4d1e9d950dca730f99b82578a0ac</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;RESPIRATORY SYSTEM&quot;" target="&quot;LONG PHRASES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Respiratory System is crucial for sustaining long phrases in singing and exchanging blood gases."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-573b4d1e9d950dca730f99b82578a0ac</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;RESPIRATORY SYSTEM&quot;" target="&quot;SUPPORT LONG PHRASES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Respiratory System is crucial for sustaining long phrases in singing and exchanging blood gases."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-573b4d1e9d950dca730f99b82578a0ac</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;EXCHANGE OF BLOOD GASES&quot;" target="&quot;ESSENTIAL FOR BREATHING&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Breathing is essential for the exchange of blood gases—oxygen in, carbon dioxide out."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-573b4d1e9d950dca730f99b82578a0ac</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;FRESH OXYGEN&quot;" target="&quot;NEEDED BEFORE TOTAL EMPTYING&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Fresh oxygen is needed before the lungs are totally empty during sustained phrases."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-573b4d1e9d950dca730f99b82578a0ac</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;MISCONCEPTIONS&quot;" target="&quot;COMMON ABOUT BREATHING&quot;">
  <data key="d4">12.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Misconceptions about breathing for singing are common and need to be dispelled."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-573b4d1e9d950dca730f99b82578a0ac</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;SOUND SOURCE&quot;" target="&quot;USED BY HUMAN VOICE AND TRUMPET&quot;">
  <data key="d4">18.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Both the human voice and a trumpet use flaps of tissue as a sound source."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-573b4d1e9d950dca730f99b82578a0ac</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;RESONATOR&quot;" target="&quot;USED BY HUMAN VOICE AND TRUMPET&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Both the human voice and a trumpet use hollow tubes as resonators."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-573b4d1e9d950dca730f99b82578a0ac</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;STORAGE DEPOT&quot;" target="&quot;ACT AS AIR RESERVOIR&quot;">
  <data key="d4">14.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The respiratory system acts as a storage depot for the air used to produce sound."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-573b4d1e9d950dca730f99b82578a0ac</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CONFLICT&quot;" target="&quot;BETWEEN SUSTAINED PHRASES AND FRESH OXYGEN&quot;">
  <data key="d4">12.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"There can be a conflict between sustaining a long phrase and needing fresh oxygen."|&gt;</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-573b4d1e9d950dca730f99b82578a0ac</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;DIAPHRAGM&quot;" target="&quot;INSPIRATORY FUNCTION&quot;">
  <data key="d4">9.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Diaphragm serves an Inspiratory Function by contracting to enlarge the thorax and facilitate inhalation."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-3fb90ae6bf97fbc21cb066ced098ee6c</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;DIAPHRAGM&quot;" target="&quot;STERNUM&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The Diaphragm originates from the bottom of the Sternum, attaching to the base of the chest."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-3fb90ae6bf97fbc21cb066ced098ee6c</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;DIAPHRAGM&quot;" target="&quot;BACTERIUM&quot;">
  <data key="d4">3.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Both the diaphragm and bacteria are living organisms, but they function in vastly different scales and contexts, with the diaphragm being part of the respiratory system and bacteria being microorganisms."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-116b7be2fde255bf1bbeef908b472818</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;DIAPHRAGM&quot;" target="&quot;TRACHEA&quot;">
  <data key="d4">16.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The diaphragm works in conjunction with the trachea to facilitate breathing by creating negative pressure that draws air into the lungs."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-116b7be2fde255bf1bbeef908b472818</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;DIAPHRAGM&quot;" target="&quot;BRONCHI&quot;">
  <data key="d4">7.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The diaphragm's movement affects the bronchi by increasing the volume of the chest cavity, allowing air to flow into the bronchi."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-116b7be2fde255bf1bbeef908b472818</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;DIAPHRAGM&quot;" target="&quot;STOMACH&quot;">
  <data key="d4">5.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The diaphragm's movement can affect the stomach by altering the pressure in the abdominal cavity, potentially affecting digestion."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-116b7be2fde255bf1bbeef908b472818</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;DIAPHRAGM&quot;" target="&quot;INTESTINES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">4.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"The diaphragm's movement can influence the intestines by changing the pressure in the abdominal cavity, potentially affecting peristalsis."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-116b7be2fde255bf1bbeef908b472818</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BACTERIUM&quot;" target="&quot;POPULATION GROWTH&quot;">
  <data key="d4">5.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bacteria, like Escherichia coli, can rapidly multiply, but the given figure of nearly nineteen million elephants in 750 years is unrealistic compared to bacterial population growth."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-116b7be2fde255bf1bbeef908b472818</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BACTERIUM&quot;" target="&quot;TRACHEA&quot;">
  <data key="d4">4.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bacteria, like Escherichia coli, can colonize the trachea and other parts of the respiratory system, potentially causing infections."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-116b7be2fde255bf1bbeef908b472818</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BACTERIUM&quot;" target="&quot;STOMACH&quot;">
  <data key="d4">3.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bacteria, like Escherichia coli, can colonize the stomach and affect digestion, potentially causing gastrointestinal issues."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-116b7be2fde255bf1bbeef908b472818</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BACTERIUM&quot;" target="&quot;INTESTINES&quot;">
  <data key="d4">4.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bacteria, like Escherichia coli, can colonize the intestines and affect digestion and absorption of nutrients."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-116b7be2fde255bf1bbeef908b472818</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;BACTERIUM&quot;" target="&quot;PLANET&quot;">
  <data key="d4">2.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Bacteria, like Escherichia coli, exist on Earth, a planet, and their populations can be influenced by environmental factors on the planet."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-116b7be2fde255bf1bbeef908b472818</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;DARWIN&quot;" target="&quot;CHARLES ELTON&quot;">
  <data key="d4">6.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Charles Elton is less famous than Darwin but both are naturalists contributing to the field of biology."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-6b3ce1353c879e903a8fc9e1194706f7</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;MALTHUS&quot;" target="&quot;CHARLES ELTON&quot;">
  <data key="d4">5.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Malthus and Darwin are both influential figures in biology, though Elton's work is more directly linked to ecology."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-6b3ce1353c879e903a8fc9e1194706f7</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CHARLES ELTON&quot;" target="&quot;OXFORD UNIVERSITY EXPEDITION TO SPITSBERGEN&quot;">
  <data key="d4">10.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Charles Elton was part of the Oxford University Expedition to Spitsbergen, which aimed to conduct a comprehensive survey of the region."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-6b3ce1353c879e903a8fc9e1194706f7</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CHARLES ELTON&quot;" target="&quot;BEAR ISLAND&quot;">
  <data key="d4">10.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Charles Elton visited Bear Island during his expedition."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-6b3ce1353c879e903a8fc9e1194706f7</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CHARLES ELTON&quot;" target="&quot;ARCTIC&quot;">
  <data key="d4">10.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Charles Elton visited the Arctic region, specifically Bear Island, during his expedition."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-6b3ce1353c879e903a8fc9e1194706f7</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CHARLES ELTON&quot;" target="&quot;SPITSBERGEN&quot;">
  <data key="d4">10.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Charles Elton was part of the expedition that aimed to survey Spitsbergen."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-6b3ce1353c879e903a8fc9e1194706f7</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CHARLES ELTON&quot;" target="&quot;ORNITHOLOGY&quot;">
  <data key="d4">8.0</data>
  <data key="d5">"Charles Elton was part of the ornithology team during the expedition."</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-6b3ce1353c879e903a8fc9e1194706f7</data>
  <data key="d7">1</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CHARLES ELTON&quot;" target="&quot;BOTANY&quot;">
